'''Kylian Mbappé Lottin''' (born 20 December 1998) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{Spanish football updater|Real Madrid}} club [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] and [[Captain (association football)|captains]] the [[France national football team|France national team]]. Widely regarded as one of the best players in the world, he is known for his pace, dribbling, and clinical finishing.

Born in [[Paris]] and raised in nearby [[Bondy]], Mbappé began his senior club career in 2015 with [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]]. With Monaco, he won the [[Ligue 1]] title for the [[2016–17 AS Monaco FC season|2016–17 season]]. In 2017, at age 18, Mbappé signed for [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] (PSG) on an eventual permanent [[Transfer (association football)|transfer]] worth €180&nbsp;million, making him the second-[[List of most expensive association football transfers|most-expensive player]] and most expensive teenage player of all time.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/soccer-transfers/story/3388743/psg-trigger-kylian-mbappes-permanent-transfer-from-monaco |title=PSG trigger Kylian Mbappe's permanent transfer from Monaco |publisher=ESPN |date=19 February 2018 |access-date=19 February 2018 |archive-date=1 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401165055/http://www.espn.com/soccer/soccer-transfers/story/3388743/psg-trigger-kylian-mbappes-permanent-transfer-from-monaco |url-status=live}}</ref> With PSG, he won six Ligue 1 titles, four [[Coupes de France]], including a domestic [[List of association football teams to have won four or more trophies in one season|quadruple]] in the [[2019–20 Paris Saint-Germain FC season|2019–20 season]] and became the club's [[List of Paris Saint-Germain FC records and statistics#All-time top scorers|all-time top goalscorer]]. He is a record 5 time [[Ligue 1 Player of the Year]] and a record 6 time [[List of Ligue 1 top scorers|Ligue 1 top goalscorer]]. In 2024, after several years of speculation, Mbappé joined Real Madrid on a free transfer, winning the [[Pichichi Trophy]] in consecutive seasons and his first [[European Golden Shoe]] in his debut season.

At the international level, Mbappé made his senior debut for France in 2017. At the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], Mbappé became the youngest French player to score at a World Cup, as well as the second teenager, after [[Pelé]], to score in a [[List of FIFA World Cup finals|World Cup final]]. He finished as the joint second-highest goalscorer as France won the tournament, and he was honored as the [[FIFA World Cup Best Young Player Award|FIFA World Cup Best Young Player]] and [[French Player of the Year]]. He helped France to victory in the [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League]] in 2021, receiving the [[2021 UEFA Nations League Finals#Awards|top scorer award]] in [[2021 UEFA Nations League Finals|the finals]]. At the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], France reached the [[2022 FIFA World Cup final|final]] again; Mbappé won the [[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Boot|Golden Boot]] and [[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Ball|Silver Ball]], and set a new record for the [[List of FIFA World Cup final goalscorers|most goals scored in World Cup final matches]]. Mbappé, who scored a hat trick in the match, is one of only two players to have scored in two consecutive World Cup finals.

Mbappé finished in third place for the [[2023 Ballon d'Or]] and was runner-up for [[The Best FIFA Men's Player]] award of [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2022|2022]]. He has been the [[List of UEFA Champions League top scorers#Top scorers by season|UEFA Champions League top scorer]] twice. Mbappé has been named in the [[FIFA FIFPro World11]] six times, the [[IFFHS World Team#Men's winners|IFFHS Men's World Team]] five times and was awarded the [[IFFHS World's Best Top Goal Scorer]] twice. He was awarded the [[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy]] in 2017 and the [[Kopa Trophy]] in 2018. in the [[2021–22 Ligue 1|2021–22 season]], he became the first player to finish as both [[Ligue 1]] top scorer and top assist provider. Mbappé was named one of ''[[Time 100|Time]]''{{'}}s 100 most influential people in the world in 2023 and was listed by ''[[Forbes]]'' as one of the [[Forbes list of the world's highest-paid athletes|world's ten highest-paid athletes]] in 2023 and 2024.

==Early life==
Kylian Mbappé Lottin<ref name=":7">{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur58221.html |title=Kylian Mbappé |newspaper=L'Équipe |location=Paris |access-date=5 December 2022 |archive-date=23 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200823000658/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur58221.html |url-status=live }}</ref> was born on 20 December 1998<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/player/_/id/231388/kylian-mbappe |title=Kylian Mbappé: Overview |publisher=ESPN |access-date=23 August 2020 |archive-date=21 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821201159/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/player/_/id/231388/kylian-mbappe |url-status=live}}</ref> in the [[19th arrondissement of Paris]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://levestiairedusport.fr/article/kylian-mbappe-tortue-ninja-foot-francais-2/ |title=Kylian Mbappé: La Tortue Ninja du Foot Français |trans-title=The Ninja Turtle of French Football |first=Paul |last=Chevrier |website=Le Vestiaire du Sport |date=20 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404142807/http://levestiairedusport.fr/article/kylian-mbappe-tortue-ninja-foot-francais-2/ |archive-date=4 April 2019 |language=fr}}</ref> and was raised in [[Bondy]], [[Seine-Saint-Denis]], in the northeastern suburbs of [[Paris]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/kylian-mbappe-best-player-world-messi-ronaldo-psg-france-world-cup |title=Ready to take over from Messi and Ronaldo? Why Kylian Mbappe could define the next era of football |first=Julien |last=Laurens |website=FourFourTwo |publisher=Future |date=15 April 2020 |access-date=23 August 2020 |archive-date=23 April 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200423200718/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/kylian-mbappe-best-player-world-messi-ronaldo-psg-france-world-cup |url-status=live}}</ref> His father, [[Wilfrid Mbappé]], is a football coach and is originally from the [[Cameroon]]ian island of {{Interlanguage link|Djébalè|lt=Djébalè|fr}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique/20230708-cameroun-le-footballeur-kylian-mbapp%C3%A9-renoue-avec-ses-racines-%C3%A0-dj%C3%A9bal%C3%A8|title=Cameroun: le footballeur Kylian Mbappé renoue avec ses racines à Djébalè|publisher=Radio France Internationale|date=8 July 2023|accessdate=23 January 2024|language=fr|archive-date=23 January 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240123134842/https://www.rfi.fr/fr/afrique/20230708-cameroun-le-footballeur-kylian-mbapp%C3%A9-renoue-avec-ses-racines-%C3%A0-dj%C3%A9bal%C3%A8|url-status=live}}</ref> which is home to the [[Duala people|Sawa people]]. His mother and [[Sports agent|agent]], [[Fayza Lamari]], is of Algerian [[Kabyle people|Kabyle]] origin and is a former [[handball]] player.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gouaillard |first1=Frédéric |last2=Detout |first2=Arnaud |last3=Sévérac |first3=Dominique |last4=Perrin |first4=Laurent |title=Sa famille, l'avenir de son fils, l'argent : les confessions de Fayza Lamari|url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/psg/sa-famille-lavenir-de-son-fils-largent-les-confessions-de-fayza-lamari-mere-de-kylian-mbappe-06-10-2021-24OQERZEIVFQJJ7QYFES6WRFRE.php |website=Le Parisien |date=6 October 2021 |access-date=14 December 2022 |archive-date=14 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221214181353/https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/psg/sa-famille-lavenir-de-son-fils-largent-les-confessions-de-fayza-lamari-mere-de-kylian-mbappe-06-10-2021-24OQERZEIVFQJJ7QYFES6WRFRE.php |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4618402/2023/06/21/kylian-mbappe-transfer-mum-contract/ |title=Kylian Mbappe's mother and the rise of one of football's toughest dealmakers |first1=Oliver |last1=Kay |access-date=31 August 2023 |date=20 June 2023 |website=[[The Athletic]] |archive-date=31 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230831082725/https://theathletic.com/4618402/2023/06/21/kylian-mbappe-transfer-mum-contract/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.voanews.com/a/cameroon-football-fans-cheer-kylian-mbappe-french-player-africa-ties/4470675.html |title=Cameroon Football Fans Cheer for French Player with Ties to Africa |last=Kindzeka |first=Moki Edwin |publisher=Voice of America |access-date=16 July 2018 |archive-date=16 July 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180716025253/https://www.voanews.com/a/cameroon-football-fans-cheer-kylian-mbappe-french-player-africa-ties/4470675.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Youth" />}} Mbappé has a younger brother, [[Ethan Mbappé|Ethan]], who plays football for [[Lille OSC|Lille]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Brother of PSG star scores on his debut |url=https://www.pulse.ng/sports/football/kylian-mbappes-brother-ethan-scores-for-psg-in-debut-match-id8188670.html |access-date=15 July 2018 |agency=Pulse |archive-date=16 July 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180716054110/https://www.pulse.ng/sports/football/kylian-mbappes-brother-ethan-scores-for-psg-in-debut-match-id8188670.html |url-status=live|newspaper=[[Pulse Nigeria]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=15 December 2016 |title=Coupe de la Ligue: Un joueur avec des origines Algériennes marque un triplé|trans-title=Coupe de la Ligue: A player with Algerian origins scores a hat-trick |url=http://dzballon.com/coupe-de-la-ligue-un-joueur-avec-des-origines-algeriennes-marque-un-triple/|url-status=dead |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170329235143/http://dzballon.com/coupe-de-la-ligue-un-joueur-avec-des-origines-algeriennes-marque-un-triple/|archive-date=29 March 2017| access-date=29 March 2017 |website=Dzballon.com}}</ref> Their older adopted brother, [[Jirès Kembo Ekoko]], is a former professional footballer.<ref>{{cite web |date=20 December 2015 |title=Le jeune monégasque Mbappé sur les traces de Thierry Henry| trans-title= The young Monégasque Mbappé on the steps of Thierry Henry |website=Le Journal du Dimanche |url=http://www.lejdd.fr/Sport/Football/Le-jeune-monegasque-Mbappe-sur-les-traces-de-Thierry-Henry-765033|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180701194416/https://www.lejdd.fr/Sport/Football/Le-jeune-monegasque-Mbappe-sur-les-traces-de-Thierry-Henry-765033 |archive-date=1 July 2018 |access-date=2 July 2018}}</ref>

As a child, Mbappé went to a private [[Catholic school]] in Bondy, where he was considered academically gifted but unruly.<ref>{{cite web |last=Patrelle |first=Jérémy |title=10 trucs que l'on a appris sur Kylian Mbappé dans le docu 'Kylian, hors normes' de L'Équipe |url=https://www.gqmagazine.fr/lifestyle/sport/articles/10-trucs-que-lon-a-appris-sur-kylian-mbappe-dans-le-docu-kylian-hors-normes-de-lequipe-enquete/57616 |access-date=19 May 2021 |website=GQ France |date=7 November 2017 |language=fr-FR |archive-date=16 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210516051327/https://www.gqmagazine.fr/lifestyle/sport/articles/10-trucs-que-lon-a-appris-sur-kylian-mbappe-dans-le-docu-kylian-hors-normes-de-lequipe-enquete/57616 |url-status=live }}</ref> At 15, he began taking Spanish lessons, and eventually became fluent in the language.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.as.com/en/2022/02/16/soccer/1645019860_869066.html|title=Mbappé: Why does he speak fluent Spanish?|website=AS.com|date=16 February 2022|access-date=19 January 2023|archive-date=19 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230119223634/https://en.as.com/en/2022/02/16/soccer/1645019860_869066.html|url-status=live}}</ref> As a youth, Mbappé's favourite team was [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.calciomercato.com/news/l-infanzia-rossonera-di-mbappe-gli-regalammo-una-maglia-di-robin-48229 |title=L'infanzia rossonera di Mbappé: 'Gli regalammo una maglia di Robinho, ma diceva che avrebbe giocato nel Real' |language=it |trans-title=Mbappé's Rossoneri childhood: 'We gave him a Robinho shirt, but he said he would play for Real' |date=5 June 2022 |website=calciomercato.com |access-date=5 June 2022 |archive-date=5 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220605131203/https://www.calciomercato.com/news/l-infanzia-rossonera-di-mbappe-gli-regalammo-una-maglia-di-robin-48229 |url-status=live }}</ref> and he also supported [[AC Milan]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/psg/2022/05/24/628cc90822601d0d028b45b9.html |title=Mbappe: When I was young I supported AC Milan |newspaper=Marca |location=Madrid |date=24 May 2022 |access-date=7 June 2022 |archive-date=5 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220605142102/https://www.marca.com/en/football/psg/2022/05/24/628cc90822601d0d028b45b9.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/liga-francesa/2022/05/24/628caddc268e3e5b628b459a.html |title=Ligue 1: Mbappé: 'De pequeño animaba al Milan' |newspaper=Marca |location=Madrid |date=24 May 2022 |access-date=7 June 2022 |archive-date=5 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220605140121/https://www.marca.com/futbol/liga-francesa/2022/05/24/628caddc268e3e5b628b459a.html |url-status=live }}</ref> His football idols included [[Zinedine Zidane]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Magee |first=Will |date=20 January 2020 |title='Zidane was my idol as a kid': Mbappe opens up on childhood heroes |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/mbappe-reveals-that-zidane-was-his-first-idol/1lc6kly7pm20b1v7trqowscvby |access-date=31 August 2023 |website=Goal |archive-date=22 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220922104803/https://www.goal.com/en/news/mbappe-reveals-that-zidane-was-his-first-idol/1lc6kly7pm20b1v7trqowscvby |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Cristiano Ronaldo]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/soccer-transfers/story/3326678/psgs-kylian-mbappe-real-madrids-cristiano-ronaldo-was-childhood-idol |title=PSG's Kylian Mbappe: Real Madrid's Cristiano Ronaldo was childhood 'idol' |last=Garcia |first=Adriana |date=27 December 2017 |publisher=ESPN |access-date=27 December 2017 |archive-date=27 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171227201337/http://www.espn.com/soccer/soccer-transfers/story/3326678/psgs-kylian-mbappe-real-madrids-cristiano-ronaldo-was-childhood-idol |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Neymar]],<ref name=":6">{{Cite web |last=Westwood |first=James |date=29 April 2020 |title='Ronaldo, Messi & Neymar are my idols' – Mbappe says superstar trio inspired him to reach the top |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/ronaldo-messi-neymar-idols-mbappe-superstar-trio-inspired-him/1djkgwry7ohl613qgg47zuypb8 |access-date=7 May 2023 |website=Goal |language=en |archive-date=7 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230507161156/https://www.goal.com/en/news/ronaldo-messi-neymar-idols-mbappe-superstar-trio-inspired-him/1djkgwry7ohl613qgg47zuypb8 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Ronaldinho]],<ref>{{Cite web |date=7 September 2017 |title=I told Dembele to sign for Barca – Mbappe |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/barcelona/story/3198217/kylian-mbappe-i-told-ousmane-dembele-to-leave-dortmund-for-barcelona |access-date=7 May 2023 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |archive-date=7 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230507162704/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/barcelona/story/3198217/kylian-mbappe-i-told-ousmane-dembele-to-leave-dortmund-for-barcelona |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Lionel Messi]],<ref name=":6" /> [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo Nazario]],<ref>{{Cite web |last=Simpson |first=Christopher |title=PSG's Kylian Mbappe Talks of Childhood Idols Zinedine Zidane, Cristiano Ronaldo |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2872375-psgs-kylian-mbappe-talks-of-childhood-idols-zinedine-zidane-cristiano-ronaldo |access-date=11 September 2023 |website=Bleacher Report |language=en |archive-date=27 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230927235046/https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2872375-psgs-kylian-mbappe-talks-of-childhood-idols-zinedine-zidane-cristiano-ronaldo |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Eden Hazard]]<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kappel |first=David |title=Kylian Mbappe Names His 3 Idols, Snubs Lionel Messi |url=https://www.snl24.com/soccerladuma/international/messi-ronaldo-neymar-mbappe-watch/kylian-mbappe-names-his-3-idols-snubs-lionel-messi-20170918 |access-date=11 September 2023 |website=Soccer Laduma |date=18 September 2017 |language=en-US |archive-date=27 September 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230927235049/https://www.snl24.com/soccerladuma/international/messi-ronaldo-neymar-mbappe-watch/kylian-mbappe-names-his-3-idols-snubs-lionel-messi-20170918 |url-status=live }}</ref> and [[Thierry Henry]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Why Young Kylian Mbappe Spurned Chelsea and Real Madrid |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2758066-why-young-kylian-mbappe-spurned-chelsea-and-real-madrid |access-date=15 July 2018 |website=Bleacher Report |publisher=Turner |archive-date=15 July 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180715235948/https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2758066-why-young-kylian-mbappe-spurned-chelsea-and-real-madrid |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=8 July 2018 |title=Mbappe Expects 'Weird' Henry Reunion |url=https://www.beinsports.com/us/fifa-world-cup/news/mbappe-expects-weird-world-cup-reunion-with-2/923668 |access-date=18 June 2023 |website=beIN SPORTS USA |language=en-us |quote='It's going to be weird to see Thierry again. He is someone I like a lot,' the teenager told Telefoot. 'There is a lot of respect between us. He was a great player, he inspired me.' |archive-date=18 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230618122703/https://www.beinsports.com/us/fifa-world-cup/news/mbappe-expects-weird-world-cup-reunion-with-2/923668 |url-status=live }}</ref> In May 2024, just days before his transfer to Real Madrid was announced, Mbappé said that he still follows AC Milan, and would like to play for them in the future.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://sempremilan.com/kylian-mbappe-love-ac-milan-future-move | title=Mbappe professes love for Milan and hints at future move: "I watch all their matches" | date=28 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240604083056/https://sempremilan.com/kylian-mbappe-love-ac-milan-future-move |archive-date=4 June 2024}}</ref>

