When Mbappé started his career with [[AS Bondy]] at the age of six, he had several coaches, including his father. Eventually, Mbappé moved to the [[INF Clairefontaine|Clairefontaine]] football academy. His impressive performances led to numerous clubs attempting to sign him, including [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]], [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]], [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]].<ref name="Youth">{{cite news |title=Kylian Mbappe: How France World Cup star rose to prominence |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44669497 |website=BBC Sport |date=1 July 2018 |access-date=1 July 2018 |archive-date=3 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703152535/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44669497 |url-status=live}}</ref> At the age of 11, Real Madrid invited him to train with their under-12 teams.<ref>{{cite news |date=1 September 2017 |title=Kylian Mbappe joins Paris St-Germain: Why an 18-year-old is worth £166m |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40904612 |access-date=12 December 2020 |archive-date=14 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201114231644/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40904612 |url-status=live }}</ref> Mbappé was tracked by [[Stade Malherbe Caen|Caen]] for three years, but their relegation from [[Ligue 1]] in 2012 and subsequent failure to win promotion meant they could not afford to sign him.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lainé |first1=Guillaume |title=Insolite. Le jour où Kylian Mbappé aurait dû signer au SM Caen|trans-title=Unexpected. The day that Kylian Mbappé should have signed for SM Caen|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/sm-caen/monaco-manchester-city-kylian-mbappe-etait-proche-de-signer-caen-4860925 |access-date=28 May 2024 |work=[[Ouest-France]] |date=16 March 2017 |language=French}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Gaveau |first1=Claire |title=Kylian Mbappé : comment le joueur a échappé à Caen en 2012|trans-title=Kylian Mbappé: how the player escaped from Caen in 2012|url=https://www.rtl.fr/sport/football/kylian-mbappe-comment-le-joueur-a-echappe-a-caen-en-2012-7790842069 |access-date=28 May 2024 |publisher=[[RTL Group]] |date=7 November 2017 |language=French}}</ref> At age 14, Mbappé travelled to London on an invitation from Chelsea, where he played a match for their youth team against [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/transfers/arsene-wenger-likened-him-thierry-henry-but-who-arsenal-target-kylian-mbappe-a7565971.html |title=Arsene Wenger has likened him to Thierry Henry – but who is Arsenal target Kylian Mbappe? |date=6 February 2017 |newspaper=The Independent |access-date=31 May 2017 |archive-date=17 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170817084227/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/transfers/arsene-wenger-likened-him-thierry-henry-but-who-arsenal-target-kylian-mbappe-a7565971.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

===Monaco===
In July 2013, at the age of 14, Mbappé joined the youth academy of [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]]. The club managed to secure a three-year contract with him despite efforts by Real Madrid to sign him.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{Cite web |title=Les grandes dates de la jeune carrière de Kylian Mbappé (Monaco), prêté au PSG |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Les-grandes-dates-de-la-jeune-carriere-de-kylian-mbappe-monaco-prete-au-psg/828990 |access-date=31 August 2023 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr |archive-date=31 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230831003950/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Les-grandes-dates-de-la-jeune-carriere-de-kylian-mbappe-monaco-prete-au-psg/828990 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="monacoteen"/><ref>{{Cite web |title=Kylian Mbappé: The Monaco years |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/Legends/2021/02/18/kylian-mbappe-the-monaco-years-psg |access-date=31 August 2023 |website=Ligue1 |language=en |archive-date=31 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230831003952/https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/Legends/2021/02/18/kylian-mbappe-the-monaco-years-psg |url-status=live }}</ref>}}

====2015–2017: Breakthrough and league title====
In October 2015, Mbappé was brought in by [[Leonardo Jardim]] to be a mainstay in Monaco's [[reserve team]], but his level of skill and maturity prompted his promotion to the main squad after just three weeks.<ref>{{Cite news |access-date=2 May 2021 |title=Mbappe: Made in Manchester |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210504165457/https://www.skysports.com/football/story-telling/11095/12292674/kylian-mbappe-back-in-manchester-the-story-of-psg-forwards-first-champions-league-goal-for-monaco-at-the-etihad-stadium |archive-date=4 May 2021 |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/story-telling/11095/12292674/kylian-mbappe-back-in-manchester-the-story-of-psg-forwards-first-champions-league-goal-for-monaco-at-the-etihad-stadium |last=Bate |first=Adam |work=Sky Sports }}</ref> He made his first-team debut on 2 December, in a 1–1 draw against [[Stade Malherbe Caen|Caen]] in [[Ligue 1]]. The 16-year-old Mbappé became Monaco's youngest-ever first-team player, breaking the previous record set by [[Thierry Henry]] in 1994.<ref name="monacoteen">{{cite news |date=3 September 2016 |title=Kylian Mbappe: the Monaco teen who might be Europe's most wanted youngster |website=FourFourTwo |publisher=Future |url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/sg/features/kylian-mbappe-monaco-teen-who-might-be-europes-most-wanted-youngster |access-date=23 November 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170205153728/http://www.fourfourtwo.com/sg/features/kylian-mbappe-monaco-teen-who-might-be-europes-most-wanted-youngster |archive-date=5 February 2017}}</ref><ref name="soccerwayperform">{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/kylian-mbappe-lottin/377149/ |title=K. Mbappé: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250424175641/https://uk.soccerway.com/players/kylian-mbappe-lottin/377149/ |archive-date=24 April 2025 |url-status=dead}}</ref> On 20 February 2016, Mbappé scored his first goal for the first team, becoming the youngest first-team goalscorer in Monaco's history.<ref>{{cite news |title=European round-up: What you might have missed |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/35623020 |website=BBC Sport |access-date=23 February 2016 |archive-date=22 February 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160222125258/http://www.bbc.com/sport/football/35623020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Kylian Mbappe offered Monaco contract amid Arsenal, Liverpool links |url=http://www.espnfc.com/story/2814219/kylian-mbappe-offered-monaco-contract-amid-arsenal-talk |website=ESPN FC |access-date=24 February 2016 |archive-date=27 February 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160227084906/http://www.espnfc.com/story/2814219/kylian-mbappe-offered-monaco-contract-amid-arsenal-talk |url-status=live}}</ref> On 6 March, he signed his first professional contract, which kept him with Monaco until June 2019.<ref>{{cite web |date=6 March 2019 |title=First professional contract for Kylian Mbappé |url=http://www.asmonaco.com/en/article/first-professional-contract-for-kylian-mbappe-70198.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308072349/http://www.asmonaco.com/en/article/first-professional-contract-for-kylian-mbappe-70198.html|archive-date=8 March 2016|access-date=7 March 2016 |publisher=AS Monaco FC}}</ref> In an interview with [[CNN]], Monaco's vice-president [[Vadim Vasilyev (businessman)|Vadim Vasilyev]] said he knew early on that Mbappé was a "phenomenon".<ref>{{cite news |title=Kylian Mbappe: The 'phenomenon that breathes and sleeps football' |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/07/13/football/kylian-mbappe-vadim-vasilyev-monaco-france-world-cup-spt-intl/index.html |publisher=CNN |access-date=14 August 2018 |archive-date=14 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814233024/https://edition.cnn.com/2018/07/13/football/kylian-mbappe-vadim-vasilyev-monaco-france-world-cup-spt-intl/index.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

Mbappé scored the first [[Hat-trick (association football)|hat-trick]] of his first-team career on 14 December 2016, in a 7–0 home win over [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] in the [[Coupe de la Ligue]] round of 16.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2016/12/15/do-reported-arsenal-target-kylian-mbappe-smashes-21-year-old-rec/ |title=Reported Arsenal target Kylian Mbappe smashes 21-year-old record for Monaco |website=HITC Sport |date=15 December 2016 |access-date=29 January 2017 |archive-date=30 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170830102011/http://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2016/12/15/do-reported-arsenal-target-kylian-mbappe-smashes-21-year-old-rec/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ligue1.com/coupeLigue/article/monaco-mash-rennes.htm |title=Monaco mash Rennes |publisher=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=14 December 2016 |access-date=29 January 2017 |archive-date=2 February 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202033647/http://www.ligue1.com/coupeLigue/article/monaco-mash-rennes.htm |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="soccerwayperform"/>}} The following February, Mbappé scored his first Ligue 1 hat-trick in a 5–0 win over [[FC Metz|Metz]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/article/wonderkid-mbappe-nets-hat-trick-as-monaco-march-on.htm |title=Wonderkid Mbappé nets hat-trick as Monaco march on |publisher=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=11 February 2017 |access-date=16 March 2017 |archive-date=17 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317054551/http://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/article/wonderkid-mbappe-nets-hat-trick-as-monaco-march-on.htm |url-status=live}}</ref> On 5 March, he reached ten goals in Ligue 1, becoming the youngest player in thirty years to reach the mark.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/article/monaco-pull-three-points-clear-with-nantes-rout.htm |title=Monaco pull three points clear with Nantes rout |publisher=Ligue de Football Professionnel |date=5 March 2017 |access-date=16 March 2017 |archive-date=17 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317054243/http://www.ligue1.com/ligue1/article/monaco-pull-three-points-clear-with-nantes-rout.htm |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=5 March 2017 |title=Monaco, le nouveau record de précocité de Mbappé|trans-title=Monaco, the new record of precocity of Mbappé |url=http://www.goal.com/fr/news/29/ligue-1/2017/03/05/33340212/monaco-le-nouveau-record-de-pr%C3%A9cocit%C3%A9-de-mbapp%C3%A9|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170327172118/http://www.goal.com/fr/news/29/ligue-1/2017/03/05/33340212/monaco-le-nouveau-record-de-pr%C3%A9cocit%C3%A9-de-mbapp%C3%A9|archive-date=27 March 2017|access-date=16 March 2017 |website=Goal |publisher=Perform Group |language=fr}}</ref>

In the quarter-finals of the Champions League in 2017 against [[Borussia Dortmund]], Mbappé scored two goals as Monaco won the first leg 3–2.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/apr/12/borussia-dortmund-monaco-champions-league-quarter-final-first-leg-match-report |title=Kylian Mbappe gives Monaco crucial edge against Borussia Dortmund |newspaper=The Guardian |date=12 April 2017 |access-date=16 August 2018 |archive-date=16 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180816230519/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/apr/12/borussia-dortmund-monaco-champions-league-quarter-final-first-leg-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref> In the second leg, he opened the scoring as Monaco won 3–1 and advanced to the semi-finals.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Monaco 3–1 Dortmund (agg 6–3): Mbappe and Falcao send Monaco into Champions League semi-finals |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11945/10843399/monaco-3-1-dortmund-agg-6-3-mbappe-and-falcao-send-monaco-into-champions-league-semi-finals |access-date=21 August 2023 |website=Sky Sports |language=en |archive-date=21 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230821053021/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11945/10843399/monaco-3-1-dortmund-agg-6-3-mbappe-and-falcao-send-monaco-into-champions-league-semi-finals |url-status=live }}</ref> They were eventually eliminated following a 4–1 loss to [[Juventus FC|Juventus]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Dani Alves fires Juventus past Monaco into Champions League final |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/may/09/juventus-monaco-champions-league-semi-final-match-report |access-date=18 August 2023 |date=9 May 2017 |language=en |website=[[The Guardian]] |first1=Barney |last1=Ronay |archive-date=19 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230819005543/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/may/09/juventus-monaco-champions-league-semi-final-match-report |url-status=live }}</ref> Mbappé ended the 2016–17 season with 26 goals from 44 matches in all competitions, as Monaco won the Ligue 1 title.<ref name="loan">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40715851 |title=Kylian Mbappe: Paris St-Germain sign Monaco forward on loan |website=BBC Sport |date=31 August 2017 |access-date=29 June 2018 |archive-date=31 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180531090300/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40715851 |url-status=live}}</ref> He credited fellow Monaco striker [[Radamel Falcao]] as a key influence on him throughout the season, giving him the space to express himself and teaching him to be "calm" and "serene" during the game.<ref name="kuper1">{{cite web |last=Kuper |first=Simon |date=2 June 2021 |title=Kylian Mbappé is Born to Run |url=https://www.esquire.com/uk/culture/a36530130/kylian-mbappe-is-born-to-run/|access-date=23 February 2022 |website=Esquire}}</ref>

===Paris Saint-Germain===
On 31 August 2017, [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] (PSG) announced the signing of Mbappé from Monaco on loan with a mandatory purchase option of €180 million.<ref>{{cite news |date=31 August 2017 |title=Kylian Mbappé au Paris Saint-Germain! |language=fr |trans-title=Kylian Mbappé to Paris Saint-Germain! |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |url=https://www.psg.fr/pro/article/kylian-mbappe-au-paris-saint-germain|access-date=4 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170904142820/https://www.psg.fr/pro/article/kylian-mbappe-au-paris-saint-germain|archive-date=4 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=31 August 2017 |title=Kylian Mbappe transfer: PSG complete €180 million deal for Real Madrid target &#124; Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/monaco-star-mbappe-completes-180-million-paris-saint-germain-move/13k7x4cozao191hcdgpw1kkrrt |access-date=20 August 2023 |website=www.goal.com |language=en |archive-date=20 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230820194433/https://www.goal.com/en/news/monaco-star-mbappe-completes-180-million-paris-saint-germain-move/13k7x4cozao191hcdgpw1kkrrt |url-status=live }}</ref> According to PSG's assistant sporting director Luis Ferrer, Mbappé's decision to join the club was partly due to a convincing speech given by manager [[Unai Emery]] at the Mbappés' home over the summer.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gouaillard |first1=Frédéric |date=15 May 2021 |title=Transfert de Mbappé, départ de Cavani... les vérités de Luis Ferrer, l'ancien recruteur du PSG |trans-title=Mbappé transfer, Cavani departure... the truths of Luis Ferrer, former recruiter of PSG |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/psg/transfert-de-mbappe-depart-de-cavani-les-verites-de-luis-ferrer-lancien-recruteur-du-psg-15-05-2021-DAQ6RFVPIBFADP44AZ2V2QXOXI.php |access-date=23 February 2022 |website=Le Parisien |language=fr |archive-date=16 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220316022459/https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/psg/transfert-de-mbappe-depart-de-cavani-les-verites-de-luis-ferrer-lancien-recruteur-du-psg-15-05-2021-DAQ6RFVPIBFADP44AZ2V2QXOXI.php |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=15 May 2021 |title=Luis Ferrer " Je sonnais à sa porte avec des croissants à 8h ", Luis Ferrer raconte comment le PSG a recruté Mbappé en 2017 |trans-title="I was ringing at his door with croissants at 8 o'clock", Luis Ferrer tells how PSG recruited Mbappé in 2017 |url=https://www.20minutes.fr/sport/3042139-20210515-sonnais-porte-croissants-8h-luis-ferrer-raconte-comment-psg-recrute-mbappe-2017 |access-date=23 February 2022 |website=20 Minutes |language=fr |archive-date=17 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220317211133/https://www.20minutes.fr/sport/3042139-20210515-sonnais-porte-croissants-8h-luis-ferrer-raconte-comment-psg-recrute-mbappe-2017 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/kylian-mbappe/psg-comment-le-club-convaincu-kylian-mbappe-de-signer-malgre-l-intervention-du-real-madrid-et-de-6248168 |title=PSG. Comment le club a convaincu Kylian Mbappé de signer malgré l'intervention du Real Madrid et de Zinédine Zidane |website=Ouest-France |language=fr |date=5 March 2019 |access-date=15 May 2021 |archive-date=15 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210515172952/https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/kylian-mbappe/psg-comment-le-club-convaincu-kylian-mbappe-de-signer-malgre-l-intervention-du-real-madrid-et-de-6248168 |url-status=live }}</ref>}} The €180 million fee made Mbappé the most expensive teenager ever and the [[List of most expensive association football transfers|second-most-expensive player]] ever (behind his teammate [[Neymar]]), and broke the record for the largest transfer within a domestic league.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/monaco-star-mbappe-completes-180-million-paris-saint-germain/13k7x4cozao191hcdgpw1kkrrt |title=Monaco Star Mbappe Completes €180 Million Paris Saint-Germain Move |website=Goal |publisher=Perform Group |date=31 August 2017 |access-date=2 September 2017 |archive-date=2 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170902230237/http://www.goal.com/en/news/monaco-star-mbappe-completes-180-million-paris-saint-germain/13k7x4cozao191hcdgpw1kkrrt |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/psg-signs-kylian-mbappe-cleverly-skirts-financial-fair-play-process-173341772.html |title=PSG signs Kylian Mbappe, and cleverly skirts Financial Fair Play in the process |website=Yahoo Sports |date=31 August 2017 |access-date=2 September 2017 |archive-date=31 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831224330/https://sports.yahoo.com/psg-signs-kylian-mbappe-cleverly-skirts-financial-fair-play-process-173341772.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=31 August 2017 |title=Kylian Mbappé (Monaco) rejoint officiellement le PSG en prêt avec option d'achat |language=fr |trans-title=Kylian Mbappé (Monaco) officially joins PSG on loan with an option to buy |newspaper=L'Équipe |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Kylian-mbappe-monaco-rejoint-officiellement-le-psg-en-pret-avec-option/829364|url-status=live|access-date=2 September 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170902200634/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Kylian-mbappe-monaco-rejoint-officiellement-le-psg-en-pret-avec-option/829364|archive-date=2 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lci.fr/mercato/mercato-transfert-de-kylian-mbappe-monaco-et-le-psg-ont-trouve-un-accord-pour-180-millions-d-euros-2062532.html |title=Mbappe: Monaco et le PSG trouvent un accord pour 180 millions d'euros |trans-title=Mbappé: Monaco and PSG reached an agreement at 180 million euros |publisher=La Chaîne Info |language=fr |date=28 August 2017 |access-date=8 September 2017 |archive-date=1 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170901131448/http://www.lci.fr/mercato/mercato-transfert-de-kylian-mbappe-monaco-et-le-psg-ont-trouve-un-accord-pour-180-millions-d-euros-2062532.html |url-status=dead}}</ref>}} He was given the number 29 shirt upon arrival in Paris.<ref name="PSG number">{{cite web |title=Number 29 for Kylian Mbappé |url=https://en.psg.fr/pro/article/number-29-for-kylian-mbappe |quote=New Paris Saint-Germain striker Kylian Mbappé will wear the number 29 shirt. |access-date=14 September 2017 |date=2 September 2017 |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915023157/https://en.psg.fr/pro/article/number-29-for-kylian-mbappe |archive-date=15 September 2017}}</ref>

====2017–2020: Transfer and immediate success====
On 8 September 2017, Mbappé made his PSG debut, scoring a goal in a 5–1 Ligue 1 win over [[Metz FC|Metz]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41205167 |title=Metz 1–5 Paris Saint Germain |website=BBC Sport |date=8 September 2017 |access-date=10 September 2017 |archive-date=10 September 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170910050043/http://www.bbc.com/sport/football/41205167 |url-status=live}}</ref> During a 3–0 victory over [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in the group stage of the Champions League, he set up goals for [[Edinson Cavani]] and Neymar.<ref name="LES">{{cite news |title=PSG 3 Bayern Munich 0: Kylian Mbappe, Edinson Cavani and Neymar star in Champions League heavyweight battle |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/psg-3-bayern-munich-0-champions-league-kylian-mbappe-edinson-cavani-neymar-star-a3645456.html |newspaper=London Evening Standard |date=30 September 2017 |access-date=30 September 2017 |archive-date=21 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180621070344/https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/psg-3-bayern-munich-0-champions-league-kylian-mbappe-edinson-cavani-neymar-star-a3645456.html |url-status=live}}</ref> On 6 December, the 18-year-old Mbappé scored his tenth career Champions League goal in a 3–1 loss to Bayern, becoming the youngest player to reach that mark.<ref name="CL record">{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/en-au/news/mbappe-sets-new-champions-league-record-with-goal-against/q1o8gqd0r61m1589eq3okr0cy |title=Mbappe sets new Champions League record with goal against Bayern |website=Goal |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=1 July 2018 |archive-date=1 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180701164959/http://www.goal.com/en-au/news/mbappe-sets-new-champions-league-record-with-goal-against/q1o8gqd0r61m1589eq3okr0cy |url-status=live}}</ref> In July 2018, Mbappé was given the number 7 shirt for the [[2018–19 Paris Saint-Germain FC season|upcoming season]] with PSG.<ref name="number 7">{{cite news |first=Jonathan |last=Johnson |title=Kylian Mbappe gets No. 7 shirt in new-look Paris Saint-Germain kit |url=http://www.espn.co.uk/football/blog/the-toe-poke/65/post/3575253/kylian-mbappe-gets-no7-shirt-in-new-look-paris-saint-germain-kit |access-date=27 July 2018 |date=26 July 2018 |publisher=ESPN |archive-date=4 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180804224034/http://www.espn.co.uk/football/blog/the-toe-poke/65/post/3575253/kylian-mbappe-gets-no7-shirt-in-new-look-paris-saint-germain-kit |url-status=live}}</ref>

In his first appearance of the season, Mbappé scored twice in the last 10 minutes as PSG won 3–1 against [[En Avant de Guingamp|Guingamp]] in Ligue 1.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mbappe scores twice in Lique 1 return to seal PSG fight-back |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45228476 |access-date=18 August 2018 |website=BBC Sport |archive-date=14 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180914220400/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45228476 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 1 September, he scored and assisted in a 4–2 win over [[Nîmes Olympique|Nîmes]], but was [[Sent off (association football)|sent off]] for the first time in his career following an altercation with [[Téji Savanier]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/mbappe-after-red-card-i-would-do-it-again |title=Mbappe after red card: I would do it again |website=FourFourTwo |publisher=Future |date=2 September 2018 |access-date=2 September 2018 |archive-date=2 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180902220623/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/mbappe-after-red-card-i-would-do-it-again |url-status=live}}</ref> The following month, Mbappé scored four goals within 13 minutes in a 5–0 victory over [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/mbappe-breaks-45-year-ligue-1-record-in-psg-rout/d060mjliyvxe1usjx8kja4jrg |title=Mbappe breaks 45-year Ligue 1 record in PSG rout |website=Goal |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=8 October 2018 |archive-date=8 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181008174859/http://www.goal.com/en/news/mbappe-breaks-45-year-ligue-1-record-in-psg-rout/d060mjliyvxe1usjx8kja4jrg |url-status=live}}</ref> In December, he was the inaugural winner of the [[Kopa Trophy]], which is awarded by ''[[France Football]]'' to the best under-21 player in the world.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/dec/03/ballon-dor-ada-hegerberg-twerk-luka-modric |title=Ada Hegerberg: first women's Ballon d'Or marred as winner is asked to twerk |newspaper=The Guardian |first=Ed |last=Aarons |date=4 December 2018 |access-date=4 December 2018 |archive-date=23 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191023002409/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/dec/03/ballon-dor-ada-hegerberg-twerk-luka-modric |url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 January 2019, Mbappé scored a hat-trick in a 9–0 win over Guingamp.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46935009 |title=Paris St-Germain 9–0 Guingamp |website=BBC Sport |date=19 January 2019 |access-date=23 January 2019 |archive-date=23 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123224144/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46935009 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 2 March, he scored twice in a 2–1 win over Caen to reach his 50th goal with the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47417301 |title=Caen 1–2 Paris Saint Germain |website=BBC Sport |date=2 March 2019 |access-date=3 March 2019 |archive-date=25 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425121108/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/47417301 |url-status=live}}</ref> PSG finished the season as Ligue 1 champions,<ref name="ligue1history">{{cite web |date=24 May 2019 |title=Mbappe ensures PSG make Ligue 1 history despite defeat |url=https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/ligue-1/1104487/mbappe-ensures-psg-make-ligue-1-history-despite-defeat/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190525140939/https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/ligue-1/1104487/mbappe-ensures-psg-make-ligue-1-history-despite-defeat/ |archive-date=25 May 2019 |access-date=25 May 2019 |website=Fox Sports Asia}}</ref> with Mbappé winning the [[Ligue 1 Player of the Year|Player of the Year]] award<ref name="UNFP">{{cite news |date=19 May 2019 |title=Mbappé wins awards double |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/NEWS/2020/03/14/mbappe-wins-awards-double |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603092953/https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/NEWS/2020/03/14/mbappe-wins-awards-double |archive-date=3 June 2021 |access-date=20 May 2019 |publisher=Ligue 1}}</ref> and finishing the season as the [[2018–19 Ligue 1#Top goalscorers|top goalscorer]] with 33 goals.<ref name="ligue1history" />

On 3 August 2019, Mbappé scored in a 2–1 win over Rennes to capture his first title of the 2019–20 season, the [[2019 Trophée des Champions|Trophée des Champions]].<ref name="2019TDC" /> On 22 October, he scored a [[perfect hat-trick]] in a 5–0 victory over [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] in the Champions League.<ref>{{cite web |date=23 October 2019 |title=Kylian Mbappe: PSG forward sets another Champions League record with 'perfect' substitute hat-trick |url=https://www.squawka.com/en/news/kylian-mbappe-perfect-hat-trick-champions-league-manarama-prostate-cancer |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201012023625/https://www.squawka.com/en/kylian-mbappe-perfect-hat-trick-champions-league-manarama-prostate-cancer/ |archive-date=12 October 2020 |access-date=19 January 2020 |website=Squawka |publisher=Catena Media}}</ref> On 1 May 2020, PSG were crowned Ligue 1 champions after the season was cut short during the [[COVID-19 pandemic in France|COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/apr/30/psg-awarded-ligue-1-title-after-season-stopped-by-coronavirus-crisis |title=PSG awarded Ligue 1 title and two teams are relegated after season is scrapped |newspaper=The Guardian |date=30 April 2020 |access-date=13 June 2020 |archive-date=13 June 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200613025740/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/apr/30/psg-awarded-ligue-1-title-after-season-stopped-by-coronavirus-crisis |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11820/11981197/paris-saint-germain-crowned-ligue-1-champions-after-french-season-called-off |title=Paris Saint-Germain crowned Ligue 1 champions after French season called off |website=Sky Sports |date=1 May 2020 |access-date=31 May 2020 |archive-date=1 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200701213126/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11820/11981197/paris-saint-germain-crowned-ligue-1-champions-after-french-season-called-off |url-status=live}}</ref> Mbappé finished the 2019–20 season as the joint-top scorer in Ligue 1 with 18 goals, along with Monaco's [[Wissam Ben Yedder]]; Mbappé was assigned the title due to his higher goals-per-game ratio.<ref name="2019–20 Ligue 1 top scorer">{{cite web |date=1 May 2020 |title=Kylian Mbappé and Angel Di Maria: top scorer and top assist provider |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/kylian-mbappe-and-angel-di-maria-top-scorer-and-top-assist-provider |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611084210/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/kylian-mbappe-and-angel-di-maria-top-scorer-and-top-assist-provider |archive-date=11 June 2020 |access-date=1 May 2020 |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC}}</ref> After an injury during the [[2020 Coupe de France final|Coupe de France final]], Mbappé was unable to play in the [[2020 Coupe de la Ligue final|Coupe de la Ligue final]],<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2020/07/24/kylian-mbappe-ankle-injury-psg-coupe-de-france-title |title=Mbappe Injury Overshadows PSG's Coupe De France Title |magazine=Sports Illustrated |date=24 July 2020 |access-date=24 August 2020 |archive-date=1 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200801164344/https://www.si.com/soccer/2020/07/24/kylian-mbappe-ankle-injury-psg-coupe-de-france-title |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en/uefa-champions-league/news/psg-forward-mbappe-out-of-champions-league-qu/1512491 |title=PSG forward Mbappe out of Champions League quarter-final against Atalanta |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=27 July 2020 |access-date=24 August 2020 |archive-date=31 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200731070524/https://www.beinsports.com/en/uefa-champions-league/news/psg-forward-mbappe-out-of-champions-league-qu/1512491 |url-status=live}}</ref> which PSG went on to win, completing a domestic [[treble (association football)|treble]].<ref>{{cite web |date=11 August 2020 |title=Mbappe training return boosts PSG for Atalanta quarterfinal |url=https://www.sportsnet.ca/soccer/mbappe-training-return-boosts-psg-atalanta-quarterfinal/|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200829060433/https://www.sportsnet.ca/soccer/mbappe-training-return-boosts-psg-atalanta-quarterfinal/|archive-date=29 August 2020|access-date=24 August 2020 |website=Sportsnet}}</ref> He returned to action in the Champions League quarter-final against [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]] on 12 August, assisting a match-winning goal in injury time.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.as.com/en/2020/08/12/football/1597255022_750607.html |title=Atalanta dealt cruelest of exits by PSG late show |work=AS.com |date=13 August 2020 |access-date=24 August 2020 |archive-date=29 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200829055041/https://en.as.com/en/2020/08/12/football/1597255022_750607.html |url-status=live}}</ref> PSG lost 1–0 to Bayern Munich in the [[2020 UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]] on 23 August.<ref name="CL 2020">{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=573698 |title=Bayern Munich beat Paris Saint-Germain to win Champions League |publisher=ESPN |date=23 August 2020|access-date=23 August 2020|archive-date=31 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200831175653/https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=573698|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2020–2022: Further triumphs and contract extension====
Mbappé missed the first three matches of the season after contracting [[COVID-19]].<ref name=":2">{{cite news |last=Dotson |first=Kevin |date=7 September 2020 |title=Kylian Mbappe tests positive for Covid-19 while playing with France |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/09/07/football/kylian-mbappe-covid-test-spt-intl/index.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200910085351/https://www.cnn.com/2020/09/07/football/kylian-mbappe-covid-test-spt-intl/index.html |archive-date=10 September 2020 |access-date=30 September 2020 |publisher=CNN}}</ref> He returned on 20 September 2020, scoring a goal in a 3–0 win against [[OGC Nice|Nice]].<ref>{{cite web |date=20 September 2020 |title=Nice 0–3 Paris Saint-Germain |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54226147 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201012023627/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54226147 |archive-date=12 October 2020 |access-date=30 September 2020 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> In a Ligue 1 match against [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]] on 5 December, Mbappé became the fifth player to score 100 goals for PSG.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/mbappe-reaches-100-goals-for-psg-with-strike-against/36xw7k3xgagd1gf16xb9cc6xn |title=Mbappe reaches 100 goals for PSG with strike against Montpellier |website=Goal |last=Keble |first=Alex |date=5 December 2020 |access-date=5 December 2020 |archive-date=25 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125163435/https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/mbappe-reaches-100-goals-for-psg-with-strike-against/36xw7k3xgagd1gf16xb9cc6xn |url-status=live }}</ref> During the Champions League group stage, Mbappé scored two goals in a 5–1 victory over [[Başakşehir F.K.|İstanbul Başakşehir]], qualifying PSG for the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|knockout phase]].<ref>{{Cite news |last= |first= |title=PSG beat Istanbul Basaksehir in match delayed due to alleged racist incident |work= The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4229469/2020/12/09/psg-beat-istanbul-basaksehir-in-match-delayed-due-to-alleged-racist-incident/ |access-date=21 August 2023 |language=en |archive-date=21 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230821053337/https://theathletic.com/4229469/2020/12/09/psg-beat-istanbul-basaksehir-in-match-delayed-due-to-alleged-racist-incident/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He became the youngest player in Champions League history to reach twenty goals, although his record was surpassed by [[Erling Haaland]] later in the season.<ref>{{cite news |date=20 December 2020 |title=PSG star Mbappe overtakes Messi to become youngest player to reach 20 Champions League goals |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/psg-star-mbappe-overtakes-messi-to-become-youngest-player-to/iv3npfnrozd71m9ymtl13900q |access-date=20 December 2020 |website=Goal |archive-date=10 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201210193545/https://www.goal.com/en/news/psg-star-mbappe-overtakes-messi-to-become-youngest-player-to/iv3npfnrozd71m9ymtl13900q |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=10 March 2021 |title=Just how good are Kylian Mbappé and Erling Haaland? |publisher=UEFA |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0266-1199ef3658d5-145c6798f795-1000--haaland-nears-mbappe-record/ |access-date=12 March 2021 |archive-date=18 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210318000530/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0266-1199ef3658d5-145c6798f795-1000--haaland-nears-mbappe-record/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 16 February 2021, a [[List of UEFA Champions League hat-tricks|Champions League hat-trick]] saw Mbappé become PSG's [[List of Paris Saint-Germain FC records and statistics#All-time top scorers|third-highest scorer]].<ref>{{cite web |date=16 February 2021 |title=Barcelona 1–4 Paris: Mbappé hits stunning hat-trick |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0266-1197f34a1ce0-99c2ccf20bea-1000--barcelona-1-4-paris-mbappe-hits-stunning-hat-trick/ |access-date=16 February 2021 |publisher=UEFA |archive-date=16 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210216235213/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2029477--barcelona-vs-paris/postmatch/report/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=18 February 2021 |title=Champions League hits and misses: Kylian Mbappe puts Lionel Messi in the shade, Liverpool return to form |website=Sky Sports |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12220162/champions-league-hits-and-misses-kylian-mbappe-puts-lionel-messi-in-the-shade-liverpool-return-to-form |access-date=17 February 2021 |archive-date=17 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210217140644/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12220162/champions-league-hits-and-misses-kylian-mbappe-puts-lionel-messi-in-the-shade-liverpool-return-to-form |url-status=live }}</ref> On 10 March, Mbappé's goal in a 1–1 draw against Barcelona saw him surpass [[Lionel Messi]] as the youngest player to reach 25 Champions League goals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/mbappe-breaks-messi-record-youngest-player-25-champions/18w9p5utul9ax16itdzs62do8e |title=Mbappe breaks Messi record as PSG star becomes youngest player to reach 25 Champions League goals |website=Goal |date=10 March 2021 |access-date=12 March 2021 |archive-date=16 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210316102938/https://www.goal.com/en/amp/news/mbappe-breaks-messi-record-youngest-player-25-champions/18w9p5utul9ax16itdzs62do8e |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=10 March 2021 |title=Paris 1–1 Barcelona (agg: 5–2): Mbappé seals hosts' progress |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0267-11c431767556-96fc283e9856-1000--paris-1-1-barcelona-agg-5-2-mbappe-seals-hosts-progress/ |access-date=13 March 2021 |publisher=UEFA |archive-date=16 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210316000111/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2029483--paris-vs-barcelona/postmatch/report/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In the first leg of the Champions League quarter-final against Bayern Munich on 7 April, Mbappé scored two goals in PSG's 3–2 victory.<ref>{{cite web |title='I am not here to hide' – PSG star Mbappe delighted with Champions League match-winning double at Bayern Munich &#124; Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/i-am-not-here-to-hide-psg-mbappe-bayern-munich/8jqc9ld487x0145a9etxu84bi |access-date=10 April 2021 |website=Goal |archive-date=10 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210410161940/https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/i-am-not-here-to-hide-psg-mbappe-bayern-munich/8jqc9ld487x0145a9etxu84bi |url-status=live}}</ref> PSG was eliminated in the semi-finals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4215475/2021/05/03/kylian-mbappe-travels-with-psg-squad-ahead-of-city-game-amid-injury-doubts/ |title=Kylian Mbappe travels with PSG squad ahead of City game amid injury doubts |website=The Athletic |date=3 May 2021 |access-date=24 May 2021 |archive-date=5 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210505233906/https://theathletic.com/news/kylian-mbappe-injury-psg-city-latest/ayacruXrNsWB |url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 May, Mbappé had one goal and one assist as PSG won the [[2021 Coupe de France final|Coupe de France final]] against Monaco, claiming their first major trophy of the season.<ref>{{Cite news |title=PSG beat Monaco to win French Cup |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57177755 |access-date=26 May 2021 |archive-date=27 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210527045704/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57177755 |url-status=live }}</ref> He ended the Ligue 1 campaign with 27 goals, becoming the top scorer for the third consecutive season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportsmax.tv/index.php/football/international/item/82483-everyone-has-seen-mbappe-challenges-board-to-act-on-psg-s-shortcomings |title=Everyone has seen – Mbappe challenges board to act on PSG's shortcomings |website=sportsmax.tv |date=23 May 2021 |access-date=24 May 2021 |archive-date=24 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210524000351/https://www.sportsmax.tv/index.php/football/international/item/82483-everyone-has-seen-mbappe-challenges-board-to-act-on-psg-s-shortcomings |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=23 May 2021 |title=Lille end PSG dominance to win Ligue 1 title |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lille/story/4385476/lille-end-psg-dominance-to-win-ligue-1-title-for-first-time-in-10-years |access-date=26 May 2021 |publisher=ESPN |archive-date=26 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210526111629/https://www.espn.com/soccer/lille/story/4385476/lille-end-psg-dominance-to-win-ligue-1-title-for-first-time-in-10-years |url-status=live }}</ref> He also received the Ligue 1 Player of the Year award and was included in the Ligue 1 Team of the Season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.as.com/en/2021/05/23/football/1621806897_609271.html |title=Kylian Mbappé gives some clues to his future club |website=AS |date=23 May 2021 |access-date=26 May 2021 |archive-date=26 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210526164917/https://en.as.com/en/2021/05/23/football/1621806897_609271.html |url-status=dead }}</ref>

[[File:Mbappe Messi Neymar.jpg|thumb|right|Left to right: Mbappé, [[Lionel Messi]] and [[Neymar]] playing against [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] in [[Le Classique]] in October 2021|250x250px]]

On 14 August 2021, prior to PSG's opening home match of the [[2021–22 Paris Saint-Germain FC season|2021–22 season]] against [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]], Mbappé was booed by spectators amidst rumours that he wanted to sign for the Spanish club [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Bienkowski |first=Stefan |date=14 August 2021 |title=Mbappe booed ahead of PSG game as Madrid rumours intensify |url=https://www.footballtransfers.com/en/transfer-news/fr-ligue-1/2021/08/mbappe-booed-ahead-psg-game-madrid-rumours-intensify |access-date=8 January 2022 |website=FootballTransfers |archive-date=14 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221114111058/https://www.footballtransfers.com/en/transfer-news/fr-ligue-1/2021/08/mbappe-booed-ahead-psg-game-madrid-rumours-intensify |url-status=live }}</ref> Mbappé scored his first goal of the season in a 4–2 win against [[Stade Brestois 29|Brest]] six days later.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ridge |first=Patric |date=21 August 2021 |title=Brest 2–4 Paris Saint-Germain: Mbappe up and running as Messi wait continues |url=https://www.mykhel.com/football/kylian-mbappe-scores-first-goal-of-season-as-paris-saint-germain-defeat-brest-lionel-messi-173117.html |access-date=8 January 2022 |website=myKhel |archive-date=30 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220730093604/https://www.mykhel.com/football/kylian-mbappe-scores-first-goal-of-season-as-paris-saint-germain-defeat-brest-lionel-messi-173117.html |url-status=live }}</ref> On 7 December, he scored two goals in a 4–1 Champions League win over [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]], making him the youngest player in history to reach both 30 and 31 goals in the Champions League.<ref>{{cite web |date=7 December 2021 |title=Kylian Mbappé's stunning stats after Brugge |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/kylian-mbappes-stunning-stats-after-brugge-paris-saint-germain-brugge-psg-ucl |access-date=16 February 2022 |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |archive-date=29 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220729011341/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/kylian-mbappes-stunning-stats-after-brugge-paris-saint-germain-brugge-psg-ucl |url-status=live }}</ref> On 12 December, the 22-year-old Mbappé scored twice against Monaco in Ligue 1, becoming the youngest player to score 100 goals for a single top-level French team since [[Opta Sports|Opta]] began recording data during the [[1950–51 French Division 1|1950–51 season]].<ref>{{cite news |title='I give everything I have' – Mbappe becomes the youngest player to goalscoring mark with 100th PSG goal |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/i-give-everything-i-have-mbappe-becomes-the-youngest-player/blt984823dd1fad7c21 |access-date=13 December 2021 |website=Goal |archive-date=26 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221126235720/https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/i-give-everything-i-have-mbappe-becomes-the-youngest-player/blt984823dd1fad7c21 |url-status=dead }}</ref> During the Champions League round of 16, Mbappé became the second-highest goalscorer in PSG history.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.101greatgoals.com/top-stories/how-kylian-mbappe-set-a-new-record-with-his-goal-over-real-madrid/ |title=How Kylian Mbappe set a new record with his goal over Real Madrid |access-date=9 March 2022 |date=9 March 2022 |last1=Browning |first1=Ben |website=101 Great Goals |archive-date=22 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220922203224/https://www.101greatgoals.com/top-stories/how-kylian-mbappe-set-a-new-record-with-his-goal-over-real-madrid/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2022/mar/09/after-mbappes-illumination-paris-again-becomes-the-city-of-dying-light |title=After Mbappé's illumination, Paris again becomes the city of dying light |access-date=9 March 2022 |date=9 March 2022 |last1=Ronay |first1=Barney |newspaper=The Guardian |archive-date=8 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220908133633/https://www.theguardian.com/football/blog/2022/mar/09/after-mbappes-illumination-paris-again-becomes-the-city-of-dying-light |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Church |first=Ben |date=16 February 2022 |title=Champions League: Kylian Mbappe scores last-gasp winner against Real Madrid after Lionel Messi misses penalty for PSG |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2022/02/15/football/psg-real-madrid-champions-league-round-16-spt-intl/index.html |access-date=16 February 2022 |publisher=CNN |archive-date=28 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220728200810/https://www.cnn.com/2022/02/15/football/psg-real-madrid-champions-league-round-16-spt-intl/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref>}}

Despite speculations of a possible transfer to Real Madrid, Mbappé extended his contract with PSG until 2024, with a one-year optional extension.<ref>{{cite web |date=21 May 2022 |title=Kylian Mbappé extends contract with Paris Saint-Germain until 2025 |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/kylian-mbappe-extends-contract-with-paris-saint-germain-until-2025 |access-date=21 May 2022 |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |archive-date=11 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221011183825/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/kylian-mbappe-extends-contract-with-paris-saint-germain-until-2025 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/may/21/kylian-mbappe-decides-to-stay-at-psg-instead-of-joining-real-madrid|title=Kylian Mbappé decides to stay at PSG instead of joining Real Madrid|newspaper=The Guardian|first1=Ed|last1=Aarons|first2=Fabrizio|last2=Romano|date=21 May 2022|access-date=21 May 2022|archive-date=21 November 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221121144217/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/may/21/kylian-mbappe-decides-to-stay-at-psg-instead-of-joining-real-madrid|url-status=live}}</ref> According to [[Sky Sports]], Mbappé's contract included a monthly wage of £4&nbsp;million, making him the highest-paid player in the world.<ref name=":1">{{cite news |title=Kylian Mbappe: PSG forward agrees contract extension with Ligue 1 champions |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12040/12617361/kylian-mbappe-psg-forward-agrees-contract-extension-with-ligue-1-champions|access-date=26 May 2022 |website=Sky Sports }}</ref> He also reportedly received a signing-on figure in the region of £100&nbsp;million.<ref name=":1" /> With 28 goals during the season, Mbappé finished as the top scorer for the fourth consecutive time.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61537573 |title=Paris Saint Germain 5–0 Metz |website=BBC Sport |date=21 May 2022 |access-date=21 May 2022 |archive-date=15 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220815180927/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61537573 |url-status=live }}</ref> He also provided 17 assists in the season, making him the first player to finish as both top scorer and top assist provider in the league's history.<ref name=":3">{{cite web |date=21 May 2022 |title=Kylian Mbappé, une saison historique |trans-title=Kylian Mbappé, a historical season |url=https://www.ligue1.fr/Articles/ACTU/2022/05/21/kylian-mbappe-une-saison-historique |access-date=21 May 2022 |publisher=Ligue 1 |language=fr |archive-date=28 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220728201802/https://www.ligue1.fr/Articles/ACTU/2022/05/21/kylian-mbappe-une-saison-historique |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=":4">{{cite web |date=21 May 2022 |title=Meilleur buteur, meilleur passeur : Mbappé officiellement sacré ! |trans-title=Top scorer, top assist provider: Mbappé already crowned! |url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/content/meilleur-buteur-meilleur-passeur-mbappe-officiellement-sacre |access-date=21 May 2022 |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |language=fr |archive-date=30 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220730102242/https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/content/meilleur-buteur-meilleur-passeur-mbappe-officiellement-sacre |url-status=live }}</ref>

====2022–2024: All-time club goalscorer and final seasons====
On 11 October 2022, Mbappé scored a penalty kick in a 1–1 Champions League draw against [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]], becoming the leading goalscorer for PSG in European competitions with 31 goals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=11 October 2022 |title=Mbappé is the club's top European goalscorer |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/mbappe-is-the-clubs-top-european-goalscorer-sl-benfica-uefa-champions-league-2022-2023 |access-date=11 October 2022 |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |archive-date=23 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221023184858/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/mbappe-is-the-clubs-top-european-goalscorer-sl-benfica-uefa-champions-league-2022-2023 |url-status=live }}</ref> The match occurred in the midst of media reports that Mbappé wanted to leave PSG during the January [[transfer window]], which he denied.<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 October 2022 |title=What Does Kylian Mbappé Want? |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/robertkidd/2022/10/20/what-does-kylian-mbapp-want/?sh=1e32453917db |access-date=17 November 2022 |website=Forbes |archive-date=18 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221118015954/https://www.forbes.com/sites/robertkidd/2022/10/20/what-does-kylian-mbapp-want/?sh=1e32453917db |url-status=live }}</ref> On 23 January 2023, Mbappé became the first PSG player to score five goals in a match, including a ten-minute hat-trick, in a 7–0 victory over [[US Pays de Cassel|Pays de Cassel]] in the Coupe de France round of 32.<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 January 2023 |title=What Does Kylian Mbappé Want? |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/kylian-mbappe-makes-psg-history-with-5-goal-match |access-date=24 January 2023 |website=Fox Sports |archive-date=5 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230205110912/https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/kylian-mbappe-makes-psg-history-with-5-goal-match |url-status=live }}</ref> In early March, he scored his 201st goal for PSG in a 4–2 win over Nantes, becoming the club's all-time leading scorer.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 March 2023 |title=Mbappe breaks PSG's all-time scoring record |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/paris-saint-germain--frapsg/story/4861911/kylian-mbappe-breaks-edinson-cavani-paris-saint-germain-all-time-scoring-record |access-date=4 March 2023 |website=ESPN.com |language=en |archive-date=4 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230304221326/https://www.espn.com/soccer/paris-saint-germain--frapsg/story/4861911/kylian-mbappe-breaks-edinson-cavani-paris-saint-germain-all-time-scoring-record |url-status=live }}</ref> He ended the Ligue 1 campaign with 29 goals, becoming the top scorer for the fifth consecutive season as PSG won their record 11th Ligue 1 title.<ref name="2022–23 Ligue 1 top scorer">{{cite news |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/kylian-mbappe-crowned-as-ligue-1-s-top-scorer-paris-saint-germain-ligue-1-2022-2023 |title=Kylian Mbappé crowned as Ligue 1's top scorer |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |date=3 June 2023 |access-date=4 June 2023 |archive-date=4 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230604060235/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/kylian-mbappe-crowned-as-ligue-1-s-top-scorer-paris-saint-germain-ligue-1-2022-2023 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="DN">{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/psg-novamente-campeao-em-franca-com-empate-em-estrasburgo-16431023.html|title=PSG novamente campeão em França com empate em Estrasburgo|trans-title=PSG champions in France again with draw in Strasbourg|newspaper=[[Diário de Notícias]]|language=pt|date=27 May 2023|access-date=28 May 2023|archive-date=27 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230527234457/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/psg-novamente-campeao-em-franca-com-empate-em-estrasburgo-16431023.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He received the Ligue 1 Player of the Year award for the fourth consecutive season and was named in the Ligue 1 Team of the Season.<ref name="23LPY">{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=29 May 2023 |title=Kylian Mbappe named Ligue 1 Player of the Year for fourth consecutive time |url=https://www.business-standard.com/sports/football-news/kylian-mbappe-named-ligue-1-player-of-the-year-for-fourth-consecutive-time-123052900333_1.html |access-date=29 May 2023 |website=www.business-standard.com |language=en-US |archive-date=27 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231027131615/https://www.business-standard.com/sports/football-news/kylian-mbappe-named-ligue-1-player-of-the-year-for-fourth-consecutive-time-123052900333_1.html |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name="TOTY23">{{Cite web |title=Messi, Rongier, Danso... L'équipe type de la saison de Ligue 1 |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Messi-rongier-danso-l-equipe-type-de-la-saison-de-ligue-1/1399239 |access-date=29 May 2023 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr |archive-date=3 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230603053146/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Messi-rongier-danso-l-equipe-type-de-la-saison-de-ligue-1/1399239 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 13 June 2023, via an official statement released through ''[[Agence France-Presse]]'', Mbappé announced his decision not to renew his contract with PSG, which was set to expire in June 2024; according to him, the club had been informed about his decision since July 2022.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Butler |first=Michael |date=12 June 2023 |title=Kylian Mbappé stuns PSG with formal decision not to renew contract in 2024 |language=en-GB |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/jun/12/kylian-mbappe-stuns-psg-with-formal-decision-not-to-renew-contract-real-madrid |access-date=13 June 2023 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=12 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230612233330/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/jun/12/kylian-mbappe-stuns-psg-with-formal-decision-not-to-renew-contract-real-madrid |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Panja |first=Tariq |date=12 June 2023 |title=Kylian Mbappé Tells P.S.G. He Won't Extend Contract in 2024 |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/12/sports/soccer/kylian-mbappe-psg.html |access-date=13 June 2023 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=13 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230613003623/https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/12/sports/soccer/kylian-mbappe-psg.html |url-status=live }}</ref> In response to an article published by ''[[Le Parisien]]'' about his reported desire to join Real Madrid in the upcoming summer window, Mbappé [[Twitter|tweeted]] that the rumours were "lies", and reaffirmed his intention to continue at PSG.<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 June 2023 |title='LIES' – Kylian Mbappe angrily hits back at Real Madrid transfer rumours amid PSG contract uncertainty &#124; Goal.com US |url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/lies-kylian-mbappe-angrily-hits-back-real-madrid-transfer-rumours-amid-psg-contract-uncertainty/bltb08989268cb94864 |access-date=13 June 2023 |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |language=en-US |archive-date=13 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230613200040/https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/lies-kylian-mbappe-angrily-hits-back-real-madrid-transfer-rumours-amid-psg-contract-uncertainty/bltb08989268cb94864 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, during the unveiling of new manager [[Luis Enrique]] on 5 July, PSG president [[Nasser Al-Khelaifi]] stated that if Mbappé wanted to stay, he would have to "sign a new contract".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Summerscales |first=Robert |date=5 July 2023 |title=Nasser Al-Khelaifi On Kylian Mbappe: "We Cannot Let The Best Player In The World Right Now Leave For Free" |url=https://www.si.com/fannation/soccer/futbol/transfers/nasser-al-khelaifi-makes-statement-on-kylian-mbappe-contract |access-date=21 July 2023 |website=Futbol on FanNation |language=en |archive-date=21 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230721223602/https://www.si.com/fannation/soccer/futbol/transfers/nasser-al-khelaifi-makes-statement-on-kylian-mbappe-contract |url-status=live }}</ref> Mbappé was subsequently excluded from PSG's preseason tour in Japan.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{Cite web |date=21 July 2023 |title=The Paris squad for the Japan Tour |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/the-paris-squad-for-the-japan-tour-summer-tour-japan-tour-2023 |access-date=22 July 2023 |website=Paris Saint-Germain FC |archive-date=22 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230722010514/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/the-paris-squad-for-the-japan-tour-summer-tour-japan-tour-2023 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=21 July 2023 |title=Sources: PSG may never play Mbappé again |url=https://www.espn.in/football/story/_/id/38048739/psg-axe-mbappe-tour-never-play-again-sources |access-date=22 July 2023 |website=ESPN |language=en |archive-date=27 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231027132121/https://www.espn.in/football/story/_/id/38048739/psg-axe-mbappe-tour-never-play-again-sources |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=21 July 2023 |title=PSG : non convoqué pour la tournée au Japon, Mbappé est à vendre |url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/transferts/psg-non-convoque-pour-la-tournee-au-japon-mbappe-est-a-vendre-20230721 |access-date=21 July 2023 |website=LEFIGARO |language=fr |archive-date=21 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230721212159/https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/transferts/psg-non-convoque-pour-la-tournee-au-japon-mbappe-est-a-vendre-20230721 |url-status=live }}</ref>}} After much speculation surrounding his future at PSG, a statement from the club on 13 August confirmed his reintegration into the first team.<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 August 2023 |title=Kylian Mbappé has been reintegrated into first team training |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/kylian-mbappe-has-been-reintegrated-into-first-team-training-psg-paris-saint-germain-ligue-1-2023-2024 |access-date=15 August 2023 |website=Paris Saint-Germain FC |archive-date=15 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230815135651/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/kylian-mbappe-has-been-reintegrated-into-first-team-training-psg-paris-saint-germain-ligue-1-2023-2024 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=13 August 2023 |title=Kylian Mbappe returns to PSG squad |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2023/8/13/star-forward-kylian-mbappe-reinstated-by-psg |access-date=15 August 2023 |website=Al Jazeera |language=en |archive-date=14 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230814231148/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2023/8/13/star-forward-kylian-mbappe-reinstated-by-psg |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 26 August, Mbappé scored his 150th Ligue 1 goal for PSG in a 3–1 win over [[RC Lens|Lens]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mbappé scores twice on Parc des Princes return, Marseille struggles in French league |url=https://apnews.com/article/french-league-marseille-brest-psg-lens-32725fd28cfb88eed0dd71f98514de79 |date=26 August 2023 |access-date=26 August 2023 |publisher=[[Associated Press]] |language=en |archive-date=26 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230826215830/https://apnews.com/article/french-league-marseille-brest-psg-lens-32725fd28cfb88eed0dd71f98514de79 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 11 November, he scored his first hat-trick of the season in a 3–0 win over Reims, lifting PSG to the top of the Ligue 1 standings.<ref>{{Cite news |date=11 November 2023 |title=Mbappe hat-trick lifts PSG to the top |language=en |work=Reuters |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/mbappe-hat-trick-lifts-psg-top-2023-11-11/ |access-date=11 November 2023 |archive-date=11 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231111182425/https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/mbappe-hat-trick-lifts-psg-top-2023-11-11/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 3 January 2024, Mbappé scored the second goal in a 2–0 victory over Toulouse in the [[2023 Trophée des Champions]], securing his first trophy of the season. In the process, he became the all-time top goalscorer at the [[Parc des Princes]], with 111 goals.<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 January 2024 |title=Lucas Beraldo makes Paris debut |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/lucas-beraldo-makes-paris-debut-paris-saint-germain-toulouse-fc-trophee-des-champions-2023-2024 |access-date=3 January 2024 |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain FC |archive-date=3 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240103221810/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/lucas-beraldo-makes-paris-debut-paris-saint-germain-toulouse-fc-trophee-des-champions-2023-2024 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=3 January 2024 |title=Kylian Mbappe is a history maker! PSG talisman sets new Parc des Princes record after goal in Trophee des Champions final against Toulouse |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/kylian-mbappe-history-maker-psg-parc-des-princes-record-goal-trophee-des-champions-final-toulouse/bltfea402f0bb72ae45#csb3321c17114494a2 |access-date=8 January 2024 |publisher=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |archive-date=8 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240108170531/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/kylian-mbappe-history-maker-psg-parc-des-princes-record-goal-trophee-des-champions-final-toulouse/bltfea402f0bb72ae45#csb3321c17114494a2 |url-status=live }}</ref> Four days later, Mbappé scored a hat-trick in a 9–0 win over [[US Revel|Revel]] in the round of 64 of the Coupe de France, becoming the club's all-time top scorer in the competition by bringing his goal tally to 30.<ref>{{Cite news |date=7 January 2024 |title=Revel 0–9 Paris Saint-Germain: Kylian Mbappe scores hat-trick in French Cup win |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67908686#:~:text=Kylian%20Mbappe%20scored%20a%20hat,top%20scorer%20in%20the%20cup. |access-date=8 January 2024 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |archive-date=8 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240108120911/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67908686#:~:text=Kylian%20Mbappe%20scored%20a%20hat,top%20scorer%20in%20the%20cup. |url-status=live }}</ref>

Mbappé scored his second hat-trick of the season on 19 March in a 6–2 win over Montpellier, bringing him to 250 goals in all competitions for PSG.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Jones |first=Rhys |date=17 March 2024 |title=MONTPELLIER 2–6 PARIS SAINT-GERMAIN: KYLIAN MBAPPE SCORES HAT-TRICK AS LUIS ENRIQUE'S SIDE CLOSE ON TITLE |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/ligue-1/2023-2024/montpellier-2-6-paris-saint-germain-kylian-mbappe-scores-hat-trick-as-luis-enrique-s-side-close-on-t_sto10062706/story.shtml |access-date=19 March 2024 |website=[[Eurosport]] |archive-date=18 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240318013342/https://www.eurosport.com/football/ligue-1/2023-2024/montpellier-2-6-paris-saint-germain-kylian-mbappe-scores-hat-trick-as-luis-enrique-s-side-close-on-t_sto10062706/story.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> On 10 May, he announced on social media that he would not renew his contract, and would depart PSG at the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Onyeagwara |first=Nnamdi |date=10 May 2024 |title=Kylian Mbappe confirms he will leave PSG at the end of this season |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5484933/2024/05/10/kylian-mbappe-psg-transfer-exit/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240510212734/https://theathletic.com/5484933/2024/05/10/kylian-mbappe-psg-transfer-exit/ |archive-date=10 May 2024 |access-date=10 May 2024 |publisher=The Athletic |language=en-GB}}</ref> In his final match with the club on 25 May, he secured a trophy as PSG defeated Lyon in the [[2024 Coupe de France final|Coupe de France final]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=25 May 2024 |title=PSG beat Lyon 2–1 to win French Cup final in Mbappe's farewell appearance |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/psg-beat-lyon-2-1-french-cup-final-clinch-domestic-treble-2024-05-25/ |access-date=25 May 2024 |website=[[Reuters]]}}</ref> He concluded his final season with PSG as the [[List of UEFA Champions League top scorers#Top scorers by season|Champions League joint top scorer]] with 8 goals, tied with [[Harry Kane]].<ref name="auto2">{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0285-1906eba1bea4-31faa14228af-1000--champions-league-top-scorers-2023-24-harry-kane-and-kylian-m/ |title=Champions League top scorers 2023/24: Harry Kane and Kylian Mbappé top the charts |publisher=UEFA |date=1 June 2024 }}</ref>

===Real Madrid===
On 3 June 2024, [[La Liga]] club Real Madrid announced that Mbappé had signed a five-year contract with the club, concluding a highly anticipated seven-year transfer saga.<ref name=":8">{{cite web |date=3 June 2024 |title=Official Announcement: Mbappé |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/comunicado-oficial-mbappe-03-06-2024 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240603180425/https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/comunicado-oficial-mbappe-03-06-2024 |archive-date=3 June 2024 |access-date=3 June 2024 |publisher=[[Real Madrid CF]]}}</ref><ref name=":9">{{Cite web |date=3 June 2024 |title=Mbappé signs for Real Madrid |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/mbappe-nuevo-jugador-del-real-madrid-03-06-2024 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240603194608/https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/mbappe-nuevo-jugador-del-real-madrid-03-06-2024 |archive-date=3 June 2024 |access-date=3 June 2024 |publisher=Real Madrid CF |language=en-US}}</ref> His move to Madrid had been the subject of intense speculation and negotiations, reflecting his status as one of football's most sought-after players.<ref>{{cite web |date=3 June 2024 |title=Kylian Mbappé completes Real Madrid transfer after PSG exit |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/40121124/kylian-mbappe-completes-real-madrid-transfer-psg-exit |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240829213746/https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/40121124/kylian-mbappe-completes-real-madrid-transfer-psg-exit |archive-date=29 August 2024 |access-date=3 June 2024 |publisher=ESPN}}</ref> After signing he stated: "It's a dream come true. So happy and proud to join the club of my dreams."<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 June 2024 |title=Kylian Mbappe says Real Madrid move 'a dream come true' |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c199z0819vno |access-date=3 June 2024 |publisher=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 16 July, Mbappé was unveiled as a Real Madrid player at the [[Bernabéu (stadium)|Santiago Bernabéu]], wearing the number 9 shirt. His presentation was attended by 80,000 spectators.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 July 2024 |title=Spectacular welcome for Kylian Mbappé at the Santiago Bernabéu |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/mbappe-presentado-como-nuevo-jugador-del-real-madrid-16-07-2024 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240717135944/https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/mbappe-presentado-como-nuevo-jugador-del-real-madrid-16-07-2024 |archive-date=17 July 2024 |access-date=16 July 2024 |publisher=Real Madrid CF}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last1=Cortegana |first1=Mario |last2=Corrigan |first2=Dermot |date=16 July 2024 |title=Kylian Mbappe and the story of Real Madrid's decade-long 'obsession' to sign him |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5208094/2024/07/16/kylian-mbappe-real-madrid-psg-florentino-perez/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240903035536/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5208094/2024/07/16/kylian-mbappe-real-madrid-psg-florentino-perez/ |archive-date=3 September 2024 |access-date=16 July 2024 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=10 July 2024 |title=Official Announcement: Kylian Mbappé's presentation |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/club/announcements/comunicado-oficial-10-07-2024 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240710143141/https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/club/announcements/comunicado-oficial-10-07-2024 |archive-date=10 July 2024 |access-date=10 July 2024 |publisher=Real Madrid CF}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=10 July 2024 |title=Squad number changes |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/cambios-de-dorsales-en-la-plantilla-10-07-2024 |access-date=10 July 2024 |publisher=Real Madrid CF}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Cortegana |first1=Mario |last2=Rai |first2=Guillermo |date=10 July 2024 |title=Kylian Mbappe to wear No. 9 shirt at Real Madrid |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5628702/2024/07/10/kylian-mbappe-real-madrid-shirt-number/ |access-date=10 July 2024 |publisher=The Athletic |language=en-GB}}</ref>}}

====2024–2025: Debut season goalscoring records and European Golden Shoe====
Mbappé made his debut for Real Madrid on 14 August 2024 in the [[2024 UEFA Super Cup]] against [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]], scoring the second goal of a 2–0 win.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Salamanca |first1=Rodrigo |date=14 August 2024 |title=Goals from Valverde and Mbappé earn Real Madrid a record sixth European Super Cup. |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/reports/cronica-final-supercopa-de-europa-14-08-2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240826031619/https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/reports/cronica-final-supercopa-de-europa-14-08-2024 |archive-date=26 August 2024 |access-date=14 August 2024 |publisher=Real Madrid CF}}</ref> He debuted in La Liga on 18 August, during a 1–1 draw against [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Real Madrid's Kylian Mbappe held scoreless in La Liga debut as Los Blancos earn frustrating draw at Mallorca |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/real-madrids-kylian-mbappe-held-scoreless-in-la-liga-debut-as-los-blancos-earn-frustrating-draw-at-mallorca/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240821181415/https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/real-madrids-kylian-mbappe-held-scoreless-in-la-liga-debut-as-los-blancos-earn-frustrating-draw-at-mallorca/amp/ |archive-date=21 August 2024 |access-date=19 August 2024 |work=[[CBS Sports]]|date=18 August 2024 }}</ref> On 1 September, he scored his first two La Liga goals in Madrid's 2–0 victory over [[Real Betis]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=1 September 2024 |title=Mbappe opens his LaLiga account and leads Real Madrid past Real Betis |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2024/09/01/66d4cc2746163f9c238b45cc.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240909121908/https://amp.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2024/09/01/66d4cc2746163f9c238b45cc.html |archive-date=9 September 2024 |access-date=1 September 2024 |publisher=MARCA |language=en}}</ref> Later in the month, he scored his first Champions League goal for the club during their 3–1 victory over [[VfB Stuttgart]] on the inaugural matchday of the newly formatted [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|Champions League league phase]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=17 September 2024 |title=Real Madrid 3–1 Stuttgart: UEFA Champions League 2024/25 League phase |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2042038--real-madrid-vs-stuttgart/ |access-date=18 September 2024 |publisher=UEFA |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Corrigan |first=Dermot |date=17 September 2024 |title=Real Madrid 3 Stuttgart 1: Mbappe scores on big night but issues remain for Ancelotti |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5770773/2024/09/17/real-madrid-mbappe-stuttgart/ |access-date=18 September 2024 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> On 10 December, Mbappé scored his 50th Champions League goal in a 3–2 victory against Atalanta, becoming the second-youngest player to reach the mark after [[Lionel Messi]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mukherjee |first=Soham |date=11 December 2024 |title=Kylian Mbappe reaches massive Champions League milestone only bettered by Lionel Messi with goal for Real Madrid at Atalanta |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/kylian-mbappe-reaches-massive-champions-league-milestone-lionel-messi-goal-real-madrid-atalanta/bltf9d56e8d6f9cef00#csdaa81ece0775f832 |access-date=14 December 2024 |website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]}}</ref>

On 25 January 2025, Mbappé scored his first hat-trick for Madrid in a 3–0 victory over league opponents [[Real Valladolid]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Thomas|first=Marissa|title=Real Valladolid 0–3 Real Madrid: Kylian Mbappé hits hat-trick to send Real four points clear|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cq6g7zgm00mt|publisher=BBC|work=BBC Sport|date=25 January 2025|access-date=25 January 2025|archive-date=25 January 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250125223104/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cq6g7zgm00mt|url-status=live}}</ref> With five league goals in January, he was named [[La Liga Player of the Month]].<ref name="auto">{{cite news|title=Kylian Mbappé, LALIGA EA SPORTS Player of the Month for January|url=https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/news/kylian-mbappe-laliga-ea-sports-player-of-the-month-for-january|publisher=La Liga|date=31 January 2025|access-date=31 January 2025|archive-date=31 January 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250131205122/https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/news/kylian-mbappe-laliga-ea-sports-player-of-the-month-for-january|url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 February, he recorded his first hat-trick for Madrid in the Champions League in a 3–1 win over Manchester City, securing the team's progression to the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League round of 16]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lowe |first=Sid |date=19 February 2025 |title=Mbappé hat-trick rips apart Manchester City to send Real Madrid racing through |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/feb/19/real-madrid-manchester-city-champions-league-playoff-second-leg-match-report |access-date=20 February 2025 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On 13 April, he received his first red card with Madrid after making a controversial tackle on [[Antonio Blanco (footballer)|Antonio Blanco]], which he was widely scrutinised for.<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 April 2025 |title=📸 Mbappé receives first Real Madrid red card for this tackle 😳 |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/mbapp-receives-first-real-madrid-150800727.html?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAFdBJXyUi4dLEvF4reVMBkFE4rUhDL-XOSot0HUHewm5CWIN7GJb03spmOkqhAiXK0jcoIA3tFsbSm-VKeW6Wg_b3R_AQv-HQ8HWy-ftnt62vagv5QZLorNBoePp5UBsY35sqT2dhvSvTLy9TmWxDuVMfmx14T6AGvsGrsk7gN6P |access-date=14 April 2025 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=13 April 2025 |title=Mbappé 'sorry' for rash red card - Madrid coach |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/44656783/alaves-vs-real-madrid-kylian-mbappe-sent-dangerous-tackle |access-date=14 April 2025 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> On 11 May, Mbappé's hat-trick in an ''[[El Clásico]]'' loss to Barcelona brought him to 39 goals for Madrid, breaking [[Iván Zamorano]]'s record for most goals scored by a Real Madrid player in their debut season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=11 May 2025 |title=Kylian Mbappe Breaks Historic Real Madrid Goalscoring Record in El Clasico |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/kylian-mbappe-breaks-historic-real-madrid-goalscoring-record |access-date=11 May 2025 |website=Sports Illustrated |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=11 May 2025 |title=Kylian Mbappe makes Real Madrid history! France star bags brace against Barcelona in El Clasico to beat longstanding Ivan Zamorano record |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/kylian-mbappe-real-madrid-history-france-star-bags-brace-against-barcelona-el-clasico-beat-ivan-zamorano-club-record/blt6f966d6f0ebeff67 |access-date=13 May 2025 |website= |publisher=Goal |language=en}}</ref> In his next game, Mbappé scored his 28th league goal of the season, setting a record for most goals for Real Madrid in a debut season in La Liga.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/kylian-mbappe-smashes-71-year-real-madrid-la-liga-record|title=Kylian Mbappe Smashes 71-Year Real Madrid, La Liga Record With 40th Goal|last=Langell|first=Amanda|date=14 May 2025|magazine=Sports Illustrated|access-date=15 May 2025}}</ref> Mbappé finished his La Liga campaign with 31 goals in 34 games, winning the [[Pichichi Trophy]] and the [[European Golden Shoe]] for the first time in his career.<ref name="24-25-goalscoring">{{Cite web|last=Brotherton|first=Alex|title=Kylian Mbappe wins European Golden Shoe for first time|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cdr562z5xdmo|publisher=BBC|work=BBC Sport|date=26 May 2025|access-date=26 May 2025|archive-date=26 May 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250526112420/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cdr562z5xdmo|url-status=live}}</ref> On 28 May, he was named Madrid's Player of the Season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/mbappe-jugador-cinco-estrellas-mahou-de-la-temporada-27-05-2025|title=Mbappé named Mahou Cinco Estrellas Player of the Season|publisher=Real Madrid CF|date=28 May 2025|access-date=28 May 2025|archive-date=28 May 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250528181453/https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/mbappe-jugador-cinco-estrellas-mahou-de-la-temporada-27-05-2025|url-status=live}}</ref>

====2025–2026: Second Pichichi Trophy ====
For the [[2025–26 Real Madrid CF season|2025–26 season]], Mbappé switched to the number 10 shirt.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/46071662/xabi-alonso-getting-kylian-mbappe-no-10-real-madrid-need-be|title=Getting Real Madrid's No. 10 jersey is taking Mbappé to the next level|last=Hunter|first=Graham|date=26 August 2025|website=ESPN.com}}</ref> On 16 September, he scored his 49th and 50th goals for Madrid against Marseille in a 2–1 Champions League win, becoming the fastest player to achieve this feat for Madrid since [[Cristiano Ronaldo]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Azzoni|first=Tales|title=Kylian Mbappé reaches 50-goal mark with Real Madrid|url=https://apnews.com/article/kylian-mbappe-50-goals-real-madrid-4013ca87894f723ec7cafda9dcfee1d3|publisher=Associated Press|date=16 September 2025|access-date=17 September 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Gonzalez|first=Dante|title=Kylian Mbappe scores 50th goal for Real Madrid in 64 games: How long did it take Cristiano Ronaldo?|url=https://worldsoccertalk.com/news/kylian-mbappe-scores-50th-goal-for-real-madrid-in-64-games-how-long-did-it-take-cristiano-ronaldo/|publisher=World Soccer Talk|date=16 September 2025|access-date=17 September 2025}}</ref> Late in November, Mbappé scored four goals in a 4–3 win over [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]], including the second-fastest hat-trick in Champions League history, completed in just six minutes and 42 seconds.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/47110951/kylian-mbappe-scores-2nd-fastest-champions-league-hat-trick |title=Kylian Mbappé scores 2nd-fastest Champions League hat trick |publisher=ESPN |date=26 November 2025 }}</ref> On 20 December, he scored in a 2–0 victory over [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]], equaling Cristiano Ronaldo's record of 59 goals in a calendar year for Madrid.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/dec/20/european-football-bayer-leverkusen-rb-leipzig-real-madrid-roma-juventus |title=European football: Mbappé matches Ronaldo's record as Real close on Barça |publisher=The Guardian |date=20 December 2025 }}</ref> He concluded the season with 25 [[2025–26 La Liga|La Liga]] goals, securing his second Pichichi Trophy,<ref>{{cite web |last=Arya |first=Yosua |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/kylian-mbappe-real-madrid-pichichi-cristiano-ronaldo-lionel-messi-record/blt7f14077965a3db09 |title=Real Madrid ‘Galactico’ Kylian Mbappe achieves feat only matched by Cristiano Ronaldo & Lionel Messi in the last 38 years |publisher=Goal.com |date=24 May 2026 }}</ref> while also finishing as the top scorer in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] with 15 goals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/029d-1ec1670159ea-2d1882e6a430-1000--champions-league-top-scorers-kylian-mbappe-leads/ |title=Champions League top scorers: Kylian Mbappé leads |publisher=UEFA |date=6 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
===2014–2018: Youth level and senior debut===
In July 2016, Mbappé scored five times for [[France national under-19 football team|France]] as they won the [[2016 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]]. His two goals in a 3–1 victory over [[Portugal national under-19 football team|Portugal]] in the semi-finals had helped his team reach the final.<ref name="monacoteen"/> He was included in [[2016 UEFA European Under-19 Championship#Team of the Tournament|the competition's Team of the Tournament]].<ref name=":5" /> Mbappé received his first call-up to the [[France national football team|French senior squad]] to face [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] on 25 March 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/8/main/2017/03/16/33699112/monaco-star-mbappe-given-maiden-france-call-up?ICID=HP_BN_3 |title=Monaco star Mbappé given maiden France call-up |website=Goal |publisher=Perform Group|date=16 March 2017 |access-date=16 March 2017 |archive-date=17 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317054814/http://www.goal.com/en/news/8/main/2017/03/16/33699112/monaco-star-mbappe-given-maiden-france-call-up?ICID=HP_BN_3 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|first=Esther|last=Sánchez-Infante|title=Kylian Mbappé becomes France's second youngest debutant|url=https://en.as.com/en/2017/03/26/soccer/1490530434_513666.html|website=[[Diario AS]]|date=26 March 2017|access-date=9 August 2024}}</ref> On 31 August, Mbappé scored his first senior international goal in a 2018 World Cup qualification match against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=New PSG signing Mbappe scores first goal for France|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/new-psg-signing-mbappe-scores-first-goal-for-france/1iqje7aqrmvod10emrk3igmfed|website=Goal|date=31 August 2017|access-date=9 August 2024}}</ref>

===2018–2021: FIFA World Cup triumph===
[[File:Kylian Mbappé World Cup Trophy.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Mbappé holding the World Cup trophy after France won the [[2018 FIFA World Cup final|2018 World Cup final]]]]
Mbappé was called up to the [[2018 FIFA World Cup squads#France|France squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>[https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12025/11376691/alexandre-lacazette-and-anthony-martial-on-standby-for-france-world-cup-squad-and-dimitri-payet-out "France name squad for 2018 World Cup"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704123904/http://www.skysports.com/amp/football/news/12025/11376691/alexandre-lacazette-and-anthony-martial-on-standby-for-france-world-cup-squad-and-dimitri-payet-out |date=4 July 2018 }}. Sky Sports. Retrieved 30 June 2018</ref> On 21 June, the 19-year-old Mbappé scored his first World Cup goal in a 1–0 [[2018 FIFA World Cup Group C|group stage]] win over [[Peru national football team|Peru]], which made him the youngest French goalscorer in World Cup history.<ref>{{Cite web |title=World Cup: Kylian Mbappe becomes France's youngest goalscorer in a major tournament |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/world-cup-kylian-mbappe-becomes-frances-youngest-goal-scorer-in-a-major-tournament/ |first1=Kevin |last1=Skiver |access-date=18 August 2023 |date=21 June 2018 |website=[[CBS Sports]] |archive-date=19 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230819010603/https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/world-cup-kylian-mbappe-becomes-frances-youngest-goal-scorer-in-a-major-tournament/ |url-status=live }}</ref> On 30 June, he scored two goals and was named [[Player of the match|man of the match]] in a [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#France vs Argentina|4–3 win]] over [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in the round of 16.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331537 |title=France 4–3 Argentina |date=30 June 2018 |publisher=FIFA |access-date=30 June 2018 |archive-date=30 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180630132618/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/match/300331537/ |url-status=dead}}</ref> Mbappé was the second teenager to score two goals in a World Cup match after [[Pelé]] in [[1958 FIFA World Cup|1958]].<ref>{{cite news |title=France 4–3 Argentina |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44439354 |website=BBC Sport |date=1 July 2018 |access-date=30 June 2018 |archive-date=3 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703160605/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44439354 |url-status=live}}</ref> In a post-match press conference, he stated: "It's flattering to be the second one after Pelé but let's put things into context – Pelé is in another category."<ref name="Pelé 1958">{{cite news |title=Mbappe shakes off Pelé comparisons after stunning brace |url=https://www.rte.ie/sport/world-cup-2018/2018/0630/974415-mbappe-shakes-off-pele-comparisons-after-stunning-brace/ |website=RTÉ Sport |date=1 July 2018 |access-date=1 July 2018 |archive-date=1 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180701193806/https://www.rte.ie/sport/world-cup-2018/2018/0630/974415-mbappe-shakes-off-pele-comparisons-after-stunning-brace/ |url-status=live}}</ref> On 15 July, Mbappé scored a goal in the [[2018 FIFA World Cup final|World Cup final]] as France defeated [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] 4–2.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44754965 |title=France 4–2 Croatia |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=15 July 2018 |access-date=23 August 2020 |archive-date=25 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190325011256/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44754965 |url-status=live}}</ref> He became the second teenager, after Pelé, to [[List of FIFA World Cup final goalscorers|score in a World Cup final]]. Having scored four goals in the tournament, he received the [[FIFA World Cup Best Young Player Award]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/news/157-awards-piece-2986294 |title=Golden consolation for magical Modric |date=15 July 2018 |publisher=FIFA |access-date=12 December 2020 |archive-date=19 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190219104856/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/news/157-awards-piece-2986294 |url-status=live }}</ref> Pelé congratulated him on social media.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/world-cup-2018-france-croatia-pele-kylian-mbappe-welcome-to-the-club-teenage-scorer-goal-video-a8448611.html |title='Welcome to the club' – Pele praises Kylian Mbappe for becoming the second teenager to score in a World Cup final |newspaper=The Independent |last=Twomey |first=Liam |date=15 July 2019 |access-date=16 July 2018 |archive-date=16 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180716153330/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/world-cup-2018-france-croatia-pele-kylian-mbappe-welcome-to-the-club-teenage-scorer-goal-video-a8448611.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 11 June 2019, Mbappé scored his 100th career goal in a 4–0 win over [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] in a qualifier for [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/us/euro-2020-qualifiers/news/mbappe-scores-100th-career-goal/1215634 |title=Mbappe Scores 100th Career Goal |publisher=beIN Sports |date=11 June 2019 |access-date=10 November 2019 |archive-date=10 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191110212048/https://www.beinsports.com/us/euro-2020-qualifiers/news/mbappe-scores-100th-career-goal/1215634 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/calcio-estero/2019/06/12-57904455/mbappe_nella_storia_contro_andorra_gol_numero_100_in_carriera/ |title=Mbappé nella storia: contro Andorra gol numero 100 in carriera |trans-title=Mbappé makes history: against Andorra his 100th career goal |website=TuttoSport |language=it |date=12 June 2019 |access-date=16 May 2020 |archive-date=3 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803022503/https://www.tuttosport.com/news/calcio/calcio-estero/2019/06/12-57904455/mbappe_nella_storia_contro_andorra_gol_numero_100_in_carriera/ |url-status=live}}</ref> However, the tournament was postponed for a year due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{cite news |date=17 March 2020 |title=Football: Uefa confirms Euro 2020 postponed for a year because of coronavirus crisis |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/sport/football/football-euro-2020-postponed-for-a-year-by-uefa-because-of-coronavirus-crisis-says |access-date=5 July 2021 |work=The Straits Times |location=Singapore |agency=Reuters |archive-date=1 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501030742/https://www.straitstimes.com/sport/football/football-euro-2020-postponed-for-a-year-by-uefa-because-of-coronavirus-crisis-says |url-status=live }}</ref> In September 2020, Mbappé tested positive for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]], which sidelined him for a month.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite news |title=Giroud up to second on France goals list |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54366305 |access-date=29 October 2020 |archive-date=11 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201011205413/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54366305 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=7 October 2020 |title=Giroud scores twice as France beats Ukraine 7–1 in friendly |url=https://apnews.com/article/ukraine-international-soccer-eduardo-camavinga-france-archive-a8af526e6bd28aeb7b46c574d9384f8a |access-date=19 August 2023 |website=AP News |language=en |archive-date=19 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230819023807/https://apnews.com/article/ukraine-international-soccer-eduardo-camavinga-france-archive-a8af526e6bd28aeb7b46c574d9384f8a |url-status=live }}</ref>}} On 18 May 2021, he was included in [[UEFA Euro 2020 squads#France|France's squad for Euro 2020]], his second major international tournament.<ref>{{cite news |title=Karim Benzema named in France squad for first time in six years |date=18 May 2021 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4212220/2021/05/18/karim-benzema-named-in-france-squad-for-first-time-in-six-years/ |access-date=20 May 2021 |website=The Athletic |archive-date=20 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210520061200/https://theathletic.com/news/benzema-france-euro-2020-squad/ILy40oON8OQr |url-status=live }}</ref> France made it to the [[UEFA Euro 2020 knockout phase#Round of 16|Euro 2020 round of 16]], where a 3–3 draw against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] went to a [[penalty shoot-out]]; Mbappé failed to score the decisive fifth penalty kick, and France was eliminated from the tournament.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Switzerland beat France on penalties |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51198549 |date=28 June 2021 |access-date=28 June 2021 |archive-date=3 July 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210703195124/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51198549 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===2021–2023: Nations League title and second consecutive World Cup final===
In the [[UEFA Nations League]] semi-final on 7 October 2021, Mbappé contributed a goal and an assist as France defeated [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] 3–2. It was his 50th appearance for the French national team.<ref>{{cite news |date=7 October 2021 |title=Theo Hernandez caps France's fightback to stun Belgium in semi-final thriller |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/oct/07/belgium-france-nations-league-semi-final-match-report |access-date=10 October 2021 |archive-date=29 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221129004936/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/oct/07/belgium-france-nations-league-semi-final-match-report |url-status=live }}</ref> Three days later, in the [[2021 UEFA Nations League final|final]] against Spain, Mbappé scored the winning goal to give France a 2–1 victory and their first Nations League title.<ref>{{cite web |date=10 October 2021 |title=Spain vs. France – Football Match Report |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report?gameId=589985 |access-date=10 October 2021 |publisher=ESPN |archive-date=5 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221105003859/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report?gameId=589985 |url-status=live }}</ref> With two goals and two assists in the Nations League Finals, Mbappé was awarded the competition's Golden Boot, known as the "[[Alipay]] Top Scorer Trophy."<ref name="2021 Nations League Top Scorer">{{cite news |date=10 October 2021 |title=UEFA Nations League finals top scorer: Kylian Mbappé |publisher=UEFA |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/news/026e-137297f2e715-0d7aed764ef3-1000/ |access-date=10 October 2021 |archive-date=17 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221117163245/https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/news/026e-137297f2e715-0d7aed764ef3-1000/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 13 November 2021, Mbappé scored four times in an 8–0 win over [[Kazakhstan national football team|Kazakhstan]] during the [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification|2022 World Cup qualifiers]].<ref>{{cite web |date=13 November 2021 |title=France 8–0 Kazakhstan: Kylian Mbappe scores four times for world champions to book Qatar place |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/world-cup-qualification-uefa/2022/world-cup-qualifying-live-france-v-kazakhstan_sto8621561/story.shtml |access-date=20 November 2021 |website=Eurosport |archive-date=27 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231027132138/https://www.eurosport.com/geoblocking.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> It was his first hat-trick in an international match, as well as the first competitive hat-trick for France since 1985.<ref>{{cite web |date=13 November 2021 |title=Kylian Mbappe nets blistering first-half hat-trick for France against Kazakhstan |url=https://www.givemesport.com/1785015-kylian-mbappe-scores-firsthalf-hattrick-for-france-in-world-cup-qualifier-vs-kazakhstan |access-date=20 November 2021 |website=GiveMeSport |archive-date=29 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220729010055/https://www.givemesport.com/1785015-kylian-mbappe-scores-firsthalf-hattrick-for-france-in-world-cup-qualifier-vs-kazakhstan |url-status=live }}</ref> During the group stage of the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar, Mbappé scored both of France's goals in a 2–1 victory over [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]], securing entry to the knockout stages and breaking the "[[Sports-related curses#European World Cup champions' curse|World Cup Champions' Curse]]".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tagoe |first=Godwin Nii Armah |date=26 November 2022 |title=France break World Cup champion's curse in style after Denmark win |url=https://sportsbrief.com/football/28838-qatar-2022-france-nonsense-champion-curse-team-reach-16/ |access-date=28 November 2022 |website=SportsBrief |archive-date=25 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230525122832/https://sportsbrief.com/football/28838-qatar-2022-france-nonsense-champion-curse-team-reach-16/ |url-status=live }}</ref> During the [[2022 FIFA World Cup final|World Cup final]] on 18 December 2022, Mbappé became the second player in history to score a hat-trick in a World Cup final.<ref>{{cite news |title=France's Mbappé Scores Hat Trick |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/siladityaray/2022/12/18/world-cup-final-live-frances-mbapp-scores-hat-trick-to-tie-argentina-3-3-in-extra-time/?sh=ec1eba939dbe#:~:text=France%27s%20Kylian%20Mbappé%20scored%20a,for%20supremacy%20on%20the%20field |access-date=18 December 2022 |website=Forbes |archive-date=21 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230221072403/https://www.forbes.com/sites/siladityaray/2022/12/18/world-cup-final-live-argentina-and-lionel-messi-beats-france-in-penalty-kicks-after-thrilling-game/#:~:text=France%27s%20Kylian%20Mbappé%20scored%20a,for%20supremacy%20on%20the%20field |url-status=live }}</ref> Argentina had a 2–0 lead over France with just over ten minutes remaining, before Mbappé scored twice in two minutes, the second being a volley after playing a [[Push and run|one-two]] with [[Marcus Thuram]]. In [[Overtime (sports)|extra time]], Argentina took the lead again, before Mbappé scored a penalty kick to even the score at 3–3. The match went to a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-out]]; Mbappé scored his penalty, but France lost the shoot-out.<ref>{{cite news|title=Argentina beat France on penalties to win World Cup after stunning final|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/dec/18/world-cup-final-argentina-france-match-report|date=18 December 2022|access-date=18 December 2022|website=The Guardian|last=Hytner|first=David|archive-date=28 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230328074407/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/dec/18/world-cup-final-argentina-france-match-report|url-status=live}}</ref> Mbappé won the tournament's [[FIFA World Cup Golden Boot|Golden Boot]] with eight goals, and became the sixth all-time top goalscorer in World Cup history with twelve goals across two World Cups, tied with Pelé.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Summerscales |first1=Robert |title=Lionel Messi And Kylian Mbappe Shoot Up The List Of All-Time Top World Cup Goalscorers |url=https://www.si.com/fannation/soccer/futbol/news/all-time-top-world-cup-goalscorers-kylian-mbappe-up-to-6th |access-date=19 December 2022 |date=18 December 2022 |website=Si.com |archive-date=27 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221227045102/https://www.si.com/fannation/soccer/futbol/news/all-time-top-world-cup-goalscorers-kylian-mbappe-up-to-6th |url-status=live }}</ref> Having scored a goal in the 2018 final, Mbappé also became the top goalscorer in World Cup finals, with four goals.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kylian Mbappe scores final hat-trick to join Sir Geoff Hurst in exclusive club |date=18 December 2022 |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/kylian-mbappe-scores-final-hat-190438340.html#:~:text=Kylian%20Mbappe%20became%20only%20the,looks%20at%20the%20two%20trebles. |access-date=19 December 2022 |website=[[Yahoo! Sports]] |archive-date=20 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221220053122/https://sports.yahoo.com/kylian-mbappe-scores-final-hat-190438340.html#:~:text=Kylian%20Mbappe%20became%20only%20the,looks%20at%20the%20two%20trebles. |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Smale |first=Simon |date=18 December 2022 |title=Kylian Mbappé nets World Cup final hat trick to prove his class, but there has to be a winner and a loser |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2022-12-19/kylian-mbappe-fifa-world-cup-final-hattrick-messi/101787976 |access-date=19 December 2022 |website=Abc.net |archive-date=18 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230218052637/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2022-12-19/kylian-mbappe-fifa-world-cup-final-hattrick-messi/101787976 |url-status=live }}</ref>

===2023–present: Captaincy, Euro semi-finals and 400 career goals===
On 21 March 2023, following the international retirement of [[Hugo Lloris]], manager [[Didier Deschamps]] named Mbappé the new [[Captain (association football)|captain]] of France ahead of their [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying]] campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Didier-deschamps-a-choisi-kylian-mbappe-comme-nouveau-capitaine-des-bleus/1387136|title=Didier Deschamps has chosen Kylian Mbappé as the new captain of the Blues|language=fr|date=21 March 2023|access-date=21 March 2023|work=L'Équipe|archive-date=20 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230320235018/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Didier-deschamps-a-choisi-kylian-mbappe-comme-nouveau-capitaine-des-bleus/1387136|url-status=live}}</ref> In his first match as captain, Mbappé led France to a 4–0 victory over the Netherlands, scoring two goals and assisting another.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65071952|title=EUROPEAN CHAMPIONSHIP QUALIFYING – GROUP B|language=en|date=24 March 2023|access-date=27 March 2023|work=[[BBC]]|archive-date=27 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230327150803/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65071952|url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 June, Mbappé scored his 40th goal for France and became the youngest player to make 70 appearances for the team.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 June 2023 |title=Equipe de France : 40e but pour Kylian Mbappé, à une longueur de Michel Platini |url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/equipe-de-france/equipe-de-france-40e-but-pour-kylian-mbappe-a-une-longueur-de-michel-platini-20230619 |access-date=21 August 2023 |website=LEFIGARO |language=fr |archive-date=21 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230821054733/https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/equipe-de-france/equipe-de-france-40e-but-pour-kylian-mbappe-a-une-longueur-de-michel-platini-20230619 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 13 October, Mbappé scored two goals in a 2–1 win over the Netherlands, securing qualification for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 October 2023 |title=Kylian Mbappé scores 2 as France beats Netherlands 2–1 to qualify for European Championship |url=https://apnews.com/article/netherlands-france-mbappe-euro2024-06e4b9cea7a6568d108996a12ac039b2 |access-date=14 October 2023 |website=AP News |language=en |archive-date=13 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231013221227/https://apnews.com/article/netherlands-france-mbappe-euro2024-06e4b9cea7a6568d108996a12ac039b2 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 18 November, Mbappé scored a [[Hat-trick (association football)|hat-trick]] and provided three assists in a [[France v Gibraltar (UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying)|14–0]] victory over [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]], France's largest-ever victory.<ref>{{Cite web |date=18 November 2023 |title=France's historic 14–0 thrashing of Gibraltar in numbers as Kylian Mbappe, Les Bleus shatter records |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/frances-historic-14-0-thrashing-of-gibraltar-in-numbers-as-kylian-mbappe-les-bleus-shatter-records/ |access-date=19 November 2023 |website=CBSSports.com |language=en |archive-date=19 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231119181801/https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/frances-historic-14-0-thrashing-of-gibraltar-in-numbers-as-kylian-mbappe-les-bleus-shatter-records/ |url-status=live }}</ref> His three goals brought him to 300 total career goals and 46 goals for France, making him France's third all-time top scorer.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=18 November 2023 |title=France-Gibraltar : un triplé, 46 buts en Bleu, 300 buts en carrière, l'incroyable soirée de Mbappé |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/equipe-de-france/france-gibraltar-un-triple-46-buts-en-bleu-300-buts-en-carriere-lincroyable-soiree-de-mbappe-18-11-2023-DAPSBUMJJJDZBCETVVKW74YIEQ.php |access-date=19 November 2023 |website=[[Le Parisien]] |language=fr-FR |archive-date=18 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231118233141/https://www.leparisien.fr/sports/football/equipe-de-france/france-gibraltar-un-triple-46-buts-en-bleu-300-buts-en-carriere-lincroyable-soiree-de-mbappe-18-11-2023-DAPSBUMJJJDZBCETVVKW74YIEQ.php |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=19 November 2023 |title=Mbappe scores 300th goal but focuses on France's record win |language=en |work=Reuters |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/mbappe-scores-300th-goal-focuses-frances-record-win-2023-11-19/ |access-date=19 November 2023 |archive-date=19 November 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231119181804/https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/mbappe-scores-300th-goal-focuses-frances-record-win-2023-11-19/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In France's final group-stage match of Euro 2024, Mbappé scored his first-ever goal at the European Championships during a 1–1 draw against Poland, which allowed France to advance to the knockout stages.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c3gggdy0x62t |title=Euro 2024: Kylian Mbappe and Robert Lewandowski both score penalties as France held by Poland |work=BBC Sport |date=25 June 2024 |access-date=26 June 2024 }}</ref> In the semi-finals, he set-up [[Randal Kolo Muani]]'s opening goal in an eventual 2–1 defeat to Spain.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/40528676/kylian-mbappe-france-euro-2024-failure-spain-exit |title=Mbappé on France exit: My Euro was a 'failure' |work=ESPN.com |language=en |date=9 July 2024 |access-date=10 July 2024 }}</ref> Following France's elimination from the tournament, Mbappé described his performance as a "failure".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tntsports.co.uk/football/euro/2024/euro-2024-kylian-mbappe-laments-own-displays-after-france-suffer-semi-final-loss-my-euro-was-a-failure_sto20016766/story.shtml |title=Euro 2024: Kylian Mbappe laments own displays after France suffer semi-final loss – 'My Euro was a failure' |last=Jones |first=Rhys |publisher=TNT Sports |language=en |date=10 July 2024 |access-date=11 July 2024 }}</ref>

On 8 June 2025, Mbappé scored his 50th goal for France during a 2–0 victory over Germany in the [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals]] third place play-off.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/news/029a-1df3af7eedc9-c3b6e51cf3f1-1000--germany-0-2-france-report-kylian-mbappe-scores-landmark-g/ |title=Germany 0–2 France report: Kylian Mbappé scores landmark goal as Les Bleus clinch Nations League third place |website=UEFA.com |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=8 June 2025 |access-date=8 June 2025}}</ref> On 9 September, he became France's second all-time top goalscorer when he scored his 52nd international goal in a 2–1 victory over Iceland during a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group D|qualifying match for the 2026 FIFA World Cup]].{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Ukraine-France &#124; European Qualifiers 2026 |url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/match/2044219--ukraine-vs-france/ |access-date=6 September 2025 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=5 September 2025 |title=Olise, Mbappe shine as France tame Ukraine in qualifying debut |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/olise-mbappe-shine-france-tame-ukraine-qualifying-debut-2025-09-05/ |access-date=6 September 2025 |work=Reuters |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=France-Iceland &#124; European Qualifiers 2026 |url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/match/2044252--france-vs-iceland/ |access-date=10 September 2025 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Pretot |first=Julien |date=9 September 2025 |title=Mbappe on the spot as France beat Iceland 2-1 in World Cup qualifier |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/mbappe-spot-france-beat-iceland-2-1-world-cup-qualifier-2025-09-09/ |access-date=10 September 2025 |work=Reuters |language=en}}</ref>}} On 13 November, Mbappé scored twice in a 4–0 win against Ukraine, reaching 400 career goals and helping his country secure qualification for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/at-26-mbappe-hits-400-career-goals-see-the-details-41948577|title=📈 At 26, Mbappé hits 400 career goals, see the details|date=13 November 2025|website=OneFootball}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c1m3k4dpkgjt|title=France 4-0 Ukraine: Kylian Mbappe double as France seal 2026 World Cup spot|last=Rose|first=Gary|date=13 November 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref> Mbappé is the youngest player to score 400 career goals since [[Pelé]] in 1964.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Yani |first=Oleksii |date=14 November 2025 |title=Kylian Mbappe joins the elite 400-goal club at 26 - but who got there fastest? |url=https://tribuna.com/en/blogs/kylian-mbappe-joins-the-elite-400goal-club-at-26-but-who-got/ |access-date=30 December 2025 |website=Tribuna.com |url-status=live}}</ref>

==Player profile==
[[File:Kylian Mbappe 2017.jpg|thumb|upright=0.65|Mbappé's movement is often highlighted as one of his most important assets.|left]]

A versatile forward, Mbappé often plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Winger|winger]], and is capable of playing on either flank, due to his capability with both feet.<ref name="better than Henry">{{cite web |date=20 February 2017 |title=Monaco teen star Mbappe doing better than Henry at same age |url=https://www.sportsnet.ca/soccer/elliott-management-becomes-new-owner-ac-milan/ |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711224544/https://www.sportsnet.ca/soccer/elliott-management-becomes-new-owner-ac-milan/ |archive-date=11 July 2018 |access-date=11 July 2018 |website=Sportsnet}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=White |first1=Adam |last2=Devin |first2=Eric |date=10 October 2017 |title=Who should play up front for France? It's time for Didier Deschamps to decide |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/oct/10/france-didier-deschamps-mbappe-lacazette-griezmann |url-status=live |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711235330/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/oct/10/france-didier-deschamps-mbappe-lacazette-griezmann |archive-date=11 July 2018}}</ref> He is capable of cutting into the centre onto his stronger right foot from the left wing, and of creating chances and providing assists for teammates from the right thanks to his vision.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref name="wonderkid">{{cite web |last=Butt |first=Muhammad |date=21 September 2017 |title=Mbappe v Rashford v Dembele: Which wonderkid has had the biggest impact so far? |url=http://www.squawka.com/en/news/mbappe-v-rashford-v-dembele-which-wonderkid-has-had-the-biggest-impact-so-far-analysis/992850#KuWFV8jCQWxgrEra.97 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711225432/http://www.squawka.com/en/news/mbappe-v-rashford-v-dembele-which-wonderkid-has-had-the-biggest-impact-so-far-analysis/992850#KuWFV8jCQWxgrEra.97 |archive-date=11 July 2018 |access-date=11 July 2018 |website=Squawka |publisher=Catena Media}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Maasdorp |first=James |date=20 April 2017 |title=Are Cristiano Ronaldo and Lionel Messi still the world's best footballers? The players breathing down their necks |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-04-20/next-worlds-best-footballer-griezmann-neymar-mbappe-dybala/8456558 |url-status=live |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170914080858/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-04-20/next-worlds-best-footballer-griezmann-neymar-mbappe-dybala/8456558 |archive-date=14 September 2017}}</ref><ref name="going home">{{cite news |last=Mladenovic |first=Igor |date=29 August 2017 |title=Kylian Mbappé going home to Paris with sights on Neymar partnership |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/aug/29/kylian-mbappe-paris-saint-germain-neymar |url-status=live |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180712004746/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/aug/29/kylian-mbappe-paris-saint-germain-neymar |archive-date=12 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Lopopolo |first=Anthony |date=21 June 2018 |title=Mbappe emerges as France's key player in victory over Peru |url=https://www.thescore.com/worldcup/news/1560738 |access-date=4 August 2018 |website=The Score |archive-date=19 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819023741/https://www.thescore.com/worldcup/news/1560738 |url-status=live }}</ref>}} He is also able to play in the [[Centre-forward|centre]] as a main [[Striker (association football)|striker]], due to his composure, clinical finishing, and eye for goal.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{cite news |last=Brown |first=Luke |date=20 March 2017 |title=Kylian Mbappé determined to stay grounded despite Real Madrid leading the race for his signature |newspaper=The Independent |location=London |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/kylian-mbapp-transfer-news-monaco-caen-goals-real-madrid-arsenal-interest-a7639651.html |url-status=live |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180716062909/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/kylian-mbapp-transfer-news-monaco-caen-goals-real-madrid-arsenal-interest-a7639651.html |archive-date=16 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Mbappe: I haven't played striker for ages |url=https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/731484/mbappe-havent-played-striker-ages/ |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180712033535/https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/731484/mbappe-havent-played-striker-ages/ |archive-date=12 July 2018 |access-date=11 July 2018 |website=foxsportsasia.com|date=15 October 2017 }}</ref><ref name="Mbappe at 19">{{cite web |date=20 December 2017 |title=Mbappe at 19: The fantastic French teenager's rapid rise |url=http://www.beinsports.com/my/ligue-1/news/mbappe-at-19-the-fantastic-french-teenagers-7/740018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180712001650/http://www.beinsports.com/my/ligue-1/news/mbappe-at-19-the-fantastic-french-teenagers-7/740018 |archive-date=12 July 2018 |access-date=11 July 2018 |website=beIN Sports}}</ref><ref name="promessa">{{cite news |last=Faltoni |first=Piero |date=11 May 2017 |title=Kylian Mbappé, promessa mantenuta |language=it |trans-title=Kylian Mbappé, promise kept |website=HuffPost Italy |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/piero-faltoni/kylian-mbappe-promessa-mantenuta_a_22079686/ |url-status=live |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180711224700/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/piero-faltoni/kylian-mbappe-promessa-mantenuta_a_22079686/ |archive-date=11 July 2018}}</ref>}}

A skilful player, Mbappé is known for his [[Dribbling (association football)|dribbling]] ability, as well as his acceleration, agility, quick feet, first touch, link-up play and creativity when in possession of the ball, as demonstrated by his use of elaborate feints, such as [[step over]]s, or sudden changes of pace or direction to beat opponents in one-on-one situations.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref name="swapping">{{cite web |url= https://www.squawka.com/en/news/how-kylian-mbappes-game-has-changed-since-swapping-monaco-for-psg/1025380#wLgFiQWzAdz60L2c.97 |title=How Kylian Mbappé's game has changed since swapping Monaco for PSG |website=Squawka |publisher=Catena Media |first=Jake |last=Entwistle |date=30 March 2018 |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-date=12 July 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180712003147/https://www.squawka.com/en/news/how-kylian-mbappes-game-has-changed-since-swapping-monaco-for-psg/1025380#wLgFiQWzAdz60L2c.97 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="world at his feet">{{cite news |url= https://www.independent.ie/sport/soccer/world-cup-2018/fixtures-and-results/kylian-mbappe-the-19yearold-with-the-world-at-his-feet-37104947.html |title=Kylian Mbappe: The 19-year-old with the world at his feet |newspaper=Irish Independent |location= Dublin |date=11 July 2018 |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-date=11 July 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180711225645/https://www.independent.ie/sport/soccer/world-cup-2018/fixtures-and-results/kylian-mbappe-the-19yearold-with-the-world-at-his-feet-37104947.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=15 May 2015 |title=Sprint, dribbles, feintes: L'action affolante de Mbappé face à Lille |language=fr |trans-title=Sprint, dribbles, feints: The shocking action of Mbappé against Lille |newspaper=Le Figaro |location= Paris |url= http://sport24.lefigaro.fr/football/ligue-1/actualites/sprint-dribbles-feintes-l-action-affolante-de-mbappe-face-a-lille-859278 |url-status=live |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180711230345/http://sport24.lefigaro.fr/football/ligue-1/actualites/sprint-dribbles-feintes-l-action-affolante-de-mbappe-face-a-lille-859278 |archive-date=11 July 2018}}</ref>}} He is highly regarded for his pace and close ball control when dribbling at speed, as well as his movement, tactical intelligence, and ability to beat the defensive line by making attacking runs into space both on and off the ball.<ref name="wonderkid"/><ref name="world at his feet"/> His ability to time his runs enables him to stretch opposing defences, making him a dangerous offensive threat on counter-attacks.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref name="wonderkid"/><ref name="world at his feet"/><ref name="platform">{{cite news |url= https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/world-cup-2018-france-vs-argentina-blaise-matuidi-kylian-mbappe-lionel-messi-a8426281.html |title=World Cup 2018: How Blaise Matuidi laid the platform for Kylian Mbappe to put in the performance of the tournament |newspaper=The Independent |location= London |first=Michael |last=Cox |date=2 July 2018 |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-date=11 July 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180711210700/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/world-cup-2018-france-vs-argentina-blaise-matuidi-kylian-mbappe-lionel-messi-a8426281.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.squawka.com/en/news/petit-mbappe-is-ahead-of-henry-in-terms-of-how-he-uses-the-ball-when-running/926918#msAwIATBSQpfAoqS.97 |title=Mbappe's dribbling skills are superior to Henry's at the same age – Petit |website=Squawka |publisher=Catena Media |first=Jeorge |last=Bird |date=31 March 2017 |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-date=12 July 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180712000203/http://www.squawka.com/en/news/petit-mbappe-is-ahead-of-henry-in-terms-of-how-he-uses-the-ball-when-running/926918#msAwIATBSQpfAoqS.97 |url-status=live}}</ref>}}

During the beginning of his career, Mbappé was compared to various great players in the history of football. [[Arsène Wenger]] said Mbappé had similar qualities to Thierry Henry.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Why Monaco starlet Kylian Mbappe is similar to Thierry Henry |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37466860/why-monaco-starlet-kylian-mbappe-similar-thierry-henry |access-date=18 August 2023 |date=3 February 2017 |first1=Ian |last1=Holyman |website=[[ESPN]] |language=en |archive-date=19 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230819010148/https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37466860/why-monaco-starlet-kylian-mbappe-similar-thierry-henry |url-status=live }}</ref> Mbappé's talent and performances for France at the 2018 World Cup led him to be compared to Pelé in the media.<ref>{{cite news |last=Leicester |first=John |date=24 June 2018 |title=France's Kylian Mbappe emerges as star in World Cup spotlight |newspaper=Toronto Star |url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/worldcup/2018/06/24/frances-kylian-mbappe-emerges-as-star-in-world-cup-spotlight.html |url-status=live |access-date=11 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180712020617/https://www.thestar.com/sports/worldcup/2018/06/24/frances-kylian-mbappe-emerges-as-star-in-world-cup-spotlight.html |archive-date=12 July 2018}}</ref> Former France international player [[Nicolas Anelka]] said that Mbappé's ability to run at defences reminded him of [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]]'s performances at the [[Football at the 1996 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|1996 Olympics]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=30 August 2023 |title=Anelka tells Real Madrid target Mbappe: Be like Ronaldo, not me – Tribal Football |url=http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/anelka-tells-real-madrid-target-mbappe-be-like-ronaldo-not-me-4178742 |access-date=31 August 2023 |website=www.tribalfootball.com |archive-date=30 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180630185758/http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/anelka-tells-real-madrid-target-mbappe-be-like-ronaldo-not-me-4178742 |url-status=live }}</ref>

== Legacy ==
Mbappé is generally viewed as one of the best players of his generation, and is widely regarded as the best player in the world since the end of the [[Messi–Ronaldo rivalry]]'s dominance.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{Cite web |date=5 December 2022 |title=Is Mbappe the undisputed best of this generation? |url=https://spogonews.com/does-anyone-in-this-generation-come-close-to-mbappe/ |access-date=24 July 2023 |language=en-US |archive-date=24 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230724125533/https://spogonews.com/does-anyone-in-this-generation-come-close-to-mbappe/ |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=23 July 2018 |title=Kylian Mbappe: The Future of Football Is More than the Future |last=Lee |first=Joon |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2787035-kylian-mbappe-france-world-football-power-50 |website=[[Bleacher Report]] |access-date=24 July 2023 |archive-date=24 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230724125530/https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2787035-kylian-mbappe-france-world-football-power-50 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Jadon Sancho: Is the Borussia Dortmund teenager one of the best players in the world? |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/is-jadon-sancho-one-of-the-best-players-in-the-world-messi-ronaldo-mbappe-9752 |access-date=24 July 2023 |website=bundesliga.com – the official Bundesliga website |language=en |archive-date=24 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230724125532/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/is-jadon-sancho-one-of-the-best-players-in-the-world-messi-ronaldo-mbappe-9752 |url-status=live }}</ref>}} His individual and collective achievements, as well as his precocious development, have drawn much appraisal. Dutch international player [[Stefan de Vrij]] described Mbappé as his toughest opponent.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mbappe, not Ronaldo, the best forward I've faced – De Vrij |date=13 September 2018 |access-date=14 September 2018 |newspaper=Diario AS |url= https://en.as.com/en/2018/09/13/football/1536838496_461256.html |archive-date=14 September 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180914203533/https://en.as.com/en/2018/09/13/football/1536838496_461256.html |url-status=live}}</ref> Former French international [[Rio Mavuba]] remarked that if Mbappé had won the 2022 World Cup "he'd probably be the best French player (ever)".<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 December 2022 |title=Why the 'unstoppable' Kylian Mbappé now wears the crown as world's best player |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2022/12/18/football/kylian-mbappe-best-player-qatar-2022-messi-spt-intl/index.html |website=[[CNN]] |access-date=24 July 2023 |archive-date=4 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230604084938/https://edition.cnn.com/2022/12/18/football/kylian-mbappe-best-player-qatar-2022-messi-spt-intl/index.html |url-status=live }}</ref> During the same World Cup, [[Fox Sports]] deemed Mbappé one of the "World Cup's all-time greats" and "the best player in the world".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kylian Mbappé is already one of the World Cup's all-time greats |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/kylian-mbappe-is-already-one-of-the-world-cups-all-time-greats |access-date=24 July 2023 |website=FOX Sports |language=en-US |archive-date=24 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230724131032/https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/kylian-mbappe-is-already-one-of-the-world-cups-all-time-greats |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2020, Mbappé was named the fastest player in the world by the French newspaper ''[[Le Figaro]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kylian Mbappé the fastest player in the world? |website=Ligue 1 |url= https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/NEWS/2020/04/18/kylian-mbappe-the-fastest-player-in-the-world |publisher=Ligue de Football Professionnel |access-date=5 August 2020 |date=18 April 2020 |archive-date=3 August 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200803051606/https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/NEWS/2020/04/18/kylian-mbappe-the-fastest-player-in-the-world |url-status=live}}</ref> His performances at the club and international level saw him shortlisted for the [[Laureus World Sports Award for Sportsman of the Year|Laureus World Sportsman of the Year]] award in 2019<ref>{{Cite web |date=18 February 2019 |title=Laureus World Sportsman of the Year 2019 nominees |url=https://awards.laureus.com/nominees/sportsman/#tab-container |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180226212951/https://awards.laureus.com/nominees/sportsman/#tab%2Dcontainer |archive-date=26 February 2018 |access-date=9 May 2023 |publisher=Laureus }}</ref> and 2023.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2023 |url=https://www.laureus.com/world-sports-awards/2023 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230520033126/https://www.laureus.com/World-Sports-Awards/2023 |archive-date=20 May 2023 |access-date=31 August 2023 |website=Laureus |language=en |author1=Syroxemedia }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=17 April 2023 |title=A Parigi i Laureus World Sports Awards 2023 |url=https://sport.sky.it/altri-sport/2023/04/17/laureus-awards-2023-parigi-nominati |access-date=31 August 2023 |website=[[Sky Sport (Italy)|Sky Sport]] |language=it-IT |archive-date=31 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230831134327/https://sport.sky.it/altri-sport/2023/04/17/laureus-awards-2023-parigi-nominati |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2023, Mbappé was included on the ''[[Time 100|Time]]'' list of the 100 most influential people in the world.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Walt |first1=Vivienne |title=The 100 Most Influential People of 2023: Kylian Mbappé |url=https://time.com/collection/100-most-influential-people-2023/6269972/kylian-mbappe/ |access-date=22 April 2023 |magazine=Time |date=13 April 2023 |archive-date=22 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230422015259/https://time.com/collection/100-most-influential-people-2023/6269972/kylian-mbappe/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

In 2018, Mbappé was considered the world's most expensive player from a transfer value perspective by the [[International Centre for Sports Studies|CIES]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.football-observatory.com/IMG/sites/b5wp/2018/239/en/ |title=Updated transfer valuations: Mbappé takes the lead |publisher=International Centre for Sports Studies |first1=Raffaele |last1=Poli |first2=Roger |last2=Besson |first3=Loïc |last3=Ravenel |date=5 November 2018 |access-date=5 November 2018 |archive-date=18 December 2018 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20181218074805/http://www.football-observatory.com/IMG/sites/b5wp/2018/239/en/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In 2023, he was ranked third on the [[Forbes list of the world's highest-paid athletes|''Forbes'' list of the world's highest-paid athletes]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Knight |first=Brett |title=The World's 10 Highest-Paid Athletes 2023 |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/brettknight/2023/05/02/the-worlds-10-highest-paid-athletes-2023/ |access-date=8 May 2023 |website=Forbes |language=en |archive-date=7 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230507033219/https://www.forbes.com/sites/brettknight/2023/05/02/the-worlds-10-highest-paid-athletes-2023/ |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Forbes'' ranked him sixth on the list in 2024 and 16th in 2025.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/athletes|title=2025 World's Highest Paid Athletes|access-date=17 June 2025|archive-date= 1 June 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250601191927/https://www.forbes.com/lists/athletes/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/athletes|title=2024 World's Highest Paid Athletes|access-date=3 June 2025|archive-date=22 August 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240822100455/https://www.forbes.com/lists/athletes/}}</ref> ''[[Penske Media Corporation#Sportico|Sportico]]'' listed him as the fifth highest-paid athlete of 2023 and the ninth highest-paid athlete of 2024.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{Cite web|date=13 February 2025|title=Cristiano Ronaldo was the highest paid athlete in 2024 on a list which featured no women in the top 100|url=https://cnn.com/cnn/2025/02/13/sport/cristiano-ronaldo-top-100-highest-earning-athletes-spt|access-date=1 May 2025|publisher=[[CNN]]|language=en|archive-date=1 May 2025|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250501165110/https://www.cnn.com/cnn/2025/02/13/sport/cristiano-ronaldo-top-100-highest-earning-athletes-spt|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=13 February 2025 |title=Cristiano Ronaldo tops list of highest-paid athletes, Ben Simmons the only Australian, no women in top 100|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/rcna192011|access-date=3 June 2025 |publisher=[[NBC News]]|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=13 February 2025 |title=Highest-paid athletes in the world named|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/highest-paid-athletes-cristiano-ronaldo-tyson-fury-b2697849.html|access-date=3 June 2025 |publisher=[[The Independent]]|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=13 February 2025 |title=100 Highest-Paid Athletes in the World|url=https://www.sportico.com/feature/highest-paid-athletes-in-the-world-1234765608/|access-date=1 May 2025 |publisher=Sportico|language=en}}</ref>}}

== Sponsorships and business interests ==
Mbappé has a sponsorship deal with [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]]. In 2017, he partnered with the brand to launch his signature football boots, the Kylian Mbappé Nike Hypervenom 3.<ref>{{cite news |title=Nike Just Gave AS Monaco Sensation Kylian Mbappé His First Pair of Personalised Boots |url=https://www.complex.com/sports/2017/05/nike-kylian-mbappe |agency=Complex |date=29 June 2018 |access-date=30 June 2018 |archive-date=30 June 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180630025233/https://www.complex.com/sports/2017/05/nike-kylian-mbappe |url-status=live}}</ref> In 2018, he unveiled the Nike Mercurial Superfly VI boots, which were inspired by the R9 Mercurial boots of former Brazilian striker [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Kylian Mbappé Just Leaked an Amazing New R9-Inspired Nike Mercurial Superfly VI |url=https://versus.uk.com/2018/04/kylian-mbappe-just-leaked-amazing-new-r9-inspired-nike-mercurial-superfly-vi/ |agency=Versus |date=29 June 2018 |access-date=30 June 2018 |archive-date=29 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180729011315/https://versus.uk.com/2018/04/kylian-mbappe-just-leaked-amazing-new-r9-inspired-nike-mercurial-superfly-vi/ |url-status=live}}</ref> The same year, the Swiss watchmaker [[Hublot]] signed Mbappé as a [[brand ambassador]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Kylian Mbappe |url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/kylian-mbappe/ |website=Forbes |access-date=21 May 2020 |archive-date=7 June 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200607204224/https://www.forbes.com/profile/kylian-mbappe/ |url-status=live}}</ref> In December 2021, Mbappé became a brand ambassador for [[Dior]], a partnership that was initially announced for a two-year period but is still ongoing as of 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Templeton |first=Lily |date=17 December 2021 |title=EXCLUSIVE: Dior Taps Soccer Star Kylian Mbappé As Ambassador |url=https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/feature/dior-ambassador-kylian-mbappe-soccer-football-striker-paris-saint-germain-1235020293/ |access-date=28 December 2025 |website=WWD |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=WW |first=FashionNetwork com |date=24 June 2025 |title=Jonathan Anderson announces Kylian Mbappé as new Dior ambassador |url=https://ww.fashionnetwork.com/news/Jonathan-anderson-announces-kylian-mbappe-as-new-dior-ambassador,1743219.html |access-date=28 December 2025 |website=FashionNetwork.com |language=en-WW}}</ref>

On 30 July 2024, the investment firm Coalition Capital, a subsidiary of Mbappé's company Interconnected Ventures, acquired [[Oaktree Capital Management]]'s 80% stake in [[Ligue 2]] football club [[Stade Malherbe Caen|Caen]] for a reported €15 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=31 July 2024 |title=Official &#124; Kylian Mbappé completes Caen takeover - Get French Football News |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2024/official-kylian-mbappe-completes-caen-takeover/ |access-date=31 July 2024 |language=en-US}}</ref>

Mbappé has been featured in EA Sports' [[FIFA (video game series)|''FIFA'' video game series]].<ref>[https://www.fifaindex.com/player/231747/kylian-mbappé/ "Kylian Mbappe index"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180630161533/https://www.fifaindex.com/player/231747/kylian-mbapp%C3%A9/ |date=30 June 2018 }}. FIFA Index.com. Retrieved 29 June 2018</ref> His trademark [[goal celebration]] – posing with his arms folded and hands tucked under his armpits – was inspired by his younger brother Ethan, who would celebrate in this manner when beating Kylian at ''FIFA'' video games.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{cite news |date=5 May 2017 |title=Kylian Mbappé, un chambrage avec son frère à l'origine de la célébration de ses buts |language=fr|trans-title=Kylian Mbappé, a banter with his brother at the origin of the celebration of his goals |agency=L'Equipe |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Kylian-mbappe-un-chambrage-avec-son-frere-a-l-origine-de-la-celebration-de-ses-buts/798635|url-status=live|access-date=15 July 2018|archive-date=15 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180715235827/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Kylian-mbappe-un-chambrage-avec-son-frere-a-l-origine-de-la-celebration-de-ses-buts/798635}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Kylian Mbappe reveals the class reason behind his trademark goal celebration |url=https://www.givemesport.com/1048548-kylian-mbappe-reveals-the-class-reason-behind-his-trademark-goal-celebration |access-date=15 July 2018 |website=GiveMeSport |publisher=Sports New Media |archive-date=15 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180715235756/https://www.givemesport.com/1048548-kylian-mbappe-reveals-the-class-reason-behind-his-trademark-goal-celebration |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=UPDATED FIFA 19 new celebrations and tutorial, ft Cristiano Ronaldo, Paul Pogba and Neymar |url=https://talksport.com/football/418292/fifa-19-new-celebrations-cristiano-ronaldo-paul-pogba-neymar |access-date=11 October 2018 |agency=Talksport |archive-date=30 September 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200930035507/https://talksport.com/football/418292/fifa-19-new-celebrations-cristiano-ronaldo-paul-pogba-neymar/ |url-status=live}}</ref>}} Mbappé appeared on the cover of ''[[FIFA 21]]'', ''[[FIFA 22]]'' and ''[[FIFA 23]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/christinasettimi/2020/09/14/the-worlds-highest-paid-soccer-players-2020-messi-wins-mbappe-rises/ |title=World's Highest-Paid Soccer Players: Messi Wins, Mbappe Rises |magazine=Forbes|access-date=27 September 2020|archive-date=27 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927010615/https://www.forbes.com/sites/christinasettimi/2020/09/14/the-worlds-highest-paid-soccer-players-2020-messi-wins-mbappe-rises/#7601f0671cff|url-status=live}}</ref>

== Philanthropy ==
On 22 February 2018, Mbappé and the former African strikers [[George Weah]] and [[Didier Drogba]] met with French president [[Emmanuel Macron]] and [[FIFA]] president [[Gianni Infantino]] about a sports development project in Africa.<ref>{{Cite news |year=2018 |title=Macron reçoit Weah à l'Elysée en présence de Drogba et Mbappé |language=fr |trans-title=Macron hosts Weah at the Elysée in the presence of Drogba and Mbappé |website=Paris Match |url=https://www.parismatch.com/Actu/Politique/Macron-recoit-Weah-a-l-Elysee-en-presence-de-Drogba-et-Mbappe-1465295|url-status=live|access-date=21 February 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605030601/https://amp.parismatch.com/Actu/Politique/Macron-recoit-Weah-a-l-Elysee-en-presence-de-Drogba-et-Mbappe-1465295|archive-date=5 June 2020}}</ref> Mbappé stated that the development of African sport is important to him due to his parents' African origins.<ref>{{cite news |title=Emmanuel Macron hosts meeting with Weah, Drogba and Mbappé |url=https://en.as.com/en/2018/02/23/football/1519342446_437752.html |access-date=23 August 2018 |newspaper=Diario AS |archive-date=24 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180824002310/https://en.as.com/en/2018/02/23/football/1519342446_437752.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 28 January 2019, Mbappé donated $34,000 (roughly £26,000) to a crowdfunding campaign to finance a private search mission to find football player [[Emiliano Sala]], whose light aircraft had [[2019 Piper PA-46 Malibu crash|gone missing]] over the [[English Channel]] a week earlier.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/01/28/football/emiliano-sala-crowd-funding-rescue-mission-spt-intl/index.html |title=Emiliano Sala: Kylian Mbappe donates $34,000 to crowdfunding initiative |publisher=CNN |date=28 January 2019 |access-date=10 February 2019 |archive-date=3 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803014857/https://edition.cnn.com/2019/01/28/football/emiliano-sala-crowd-funding-rescue-mission-spt-intl/index.html |url-status=live}}</ref> Sala's body was eventually recovered in the wreckage of the aircraft.<ref>{{cite news |title=Body recovered from plane which crashed into English Channel confirmed as footballer Emiliano Sala|url=https://www.itv.com/news/2019-02-07/body-recovered-from-plane-which-crashed-into-english-channel-confirmed-as-footballer-emiliano-sala/|access-date=7 February 2019|agency=ITV News|date=7 February 2019}}</ref> On 10 February, Mbappé donated £27,000 to fund a search for the plane's pilot, David Ibbotson, who was later found to have also died in the crash.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/kylian-mbappe-donation-search-emiliano-sala-pilot-david-ibbotson-cardiff-city-nantes-psg-paris-saint-a8772396.html |title=Kylian Mbappe makes incredible donation to Emiliano Sala pilot David Ibbotson's search fund |newspaper=The Independent |date=10 February 2019 |access-date=10 February 2019 |archive-date=28 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190428120146/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/european/kylian-mbappe-donation-search-emiliano-sala-pilot-david-ibbotson-cardiff-city-nantes-psg-paris-saint-a8772396.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=21 September 2022|title=Emiliano Sala: Pilot told friend doomed plane was 'dodgy'|language=en-GB|work=BBC News|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-wales-62594529|access-date=22 September 2022}}</ref>

On 19 November 2021, Mbappé and the Chinese diver [[Zhang Jiaqi (diver)|Zhang Jiaqi]] became godfather and godmother, respectively, to two baby pandas at [[Beauval Zoo]], as part of a campaign to raise awareness about the species.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsround/59336471 |title=Kylian Mbappe: French footballer becomes godfather to baby pandas |website=BBC Newsround |date=19 November 2021 |access-date=23 June 2022 |archive-date=23 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220623070405/https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsround/59336471 |url-status=live }}</ref>

==Personal life==
In a 2018 interview with ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'', Mbappé spoke about the sacrifices he made as a teenager to focus on his football development: "I did not have the moments of so-called normal people during adolescence, like going out with friends, enjoying good times." He said his life was "totally turned upside down" after he became famous.<ref name="Time">{{cite news |title=Kylian Mbappe: France striker features on Time magazine front cover |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45834258 |access-date=12 October 2018 |website=BBC Sport |archive-date=13 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181013132136/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45834258 |url-status=live}}</ref> Just over four years after making his professional debut, Mbappé had over 50 million followers on [[Instagram]], and by 2023 he had [[List of most-followed Instagram accounts|over 100 million followers]].<ref name="Time" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Kylian Mbappé becomes most-followed French personality on Instagram |url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2023/kylian-mbappe-becomes-most-followed-french-personality-on-instagram/ |access-date=22 April 2023 |website=Get Football News France |archive-date=22 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230422113644/https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2023/kylian-mbappe-becomes-most-followed-french-personality-on-instagram/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Mbappé is a practicing Christian, and is fluent in French, English, and Spanish.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.sportsmanor.com/soccer-news-kylian-mbappe-religion-what-religion-does-the-worlds-second-most-expensive-soccer-player-follow/ |title=Kylian Mbappe's Religion: What Religion Does the World's Second-Most Expensive Soccer Player Follow? |first=Aliasgar |last=Ayaz |website=Sportsmanor |date=14 December 2022 |access-date=18 December 2022 |archive-date=24 January 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230124230736/https://www.sportsmanor.com/soccer-news-kylian-mbappe-religion-what-religion-does-the-worlds-second-most-expensive-soccer-player-follow/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=13 August 2023 |title=How many languages does Kylian Mbappe speak? |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/how-many-languages-does-kylian-mbappe-speak-35107525 |access-date=13 August 2023 |website=OneFootball |language=en |archive-date=13 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230813225708/https://onefootball.com/en/news/how-many-languages-does-kylian-mbappe-speak-35107525 |url-status=live }}</ref>

At a press conference during [[UEFA Euro 2024]], Mbappé encouraged French young people to vote against what he called "extreme views" in the [[2024 French legislative election]].<ref>{{cite news |title=France captain Kylian Mbappé urges vote against rising 'extremes' in election |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/jun/17/kylian-mbappe-french-election-comment-euro-2024-france-vote-against-extremes |access-date=29 June 2024 |work=The Guardian |date=17 June 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Kay |first1=Oliver |title=France, racial politics and why 'the Mbappe effect' is shaping a bitter election |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5584608/2024/06/24/france-kylian-mbappe-election-euro-2024/ |access-date=29 June 2024 |work=The New York Times |date=24 June 2024}}</ref> In October 2024, following a visit Mbappé made to [[Stockholm]], Swedish authorities launched a rape and sexual harassment investigation against an unnamed individual, with various media outlets linking Mbappé to the case.{{efn|group=upper-alpha|Attributed to multiple references:<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/sports/soccer/french-soccer-star-kylian-mbappe-denies-rape-report-0dd9c325|title=French Soccer Star Kylian Mbappé Denies Rape Report|first=Joshua|last=Robinson|date=16 October 2024|work=The Wall Street Journal|accessdate=19 December 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250207141924/https://www.wsj.com/sports/soccer/french-soccer-star-kylian-mbappe-denies-rape-report-0dd9c325|archive-date=7 February 2025|url-status=live|url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-12 |title=Kylian Mbappé: Swedish rape inquiry linked to footballer closed |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cgkxgd4rkexo |access-date=2026-04-19 |website=BBC |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Press |first=Associated |date=2024-12-12 |title=Swedish prosecutors drop rape investigation reportedly linked to Kylian Mbappé |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/dec/12/swedish-prosecutors-drop-investigation-reportedly-linked-to-kylian-mbappe |access-date=2026-04-19 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>}} On 12 December, the prosecution stated there was insufficient evidence to proceed with the investigation, and the case was closed.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/article/mbappe-sweden-rape-investigation-2bfffda70e9a774e88400f860f67c2d6|title=Rape investigation that Swedish media say focused on Kylian Mbappé has been closed|first=Karl|last=Ritter|publisher=Associated Press|date=12 December 2024}}</ref>

As of March 2026, Mbappé is in a relationship with the Spanish actress and model [[Ester Expósito]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=FM |first=La Rédaction |date=2026-03-31 |title=Ester Exposito sort du silence sur Kylian Mbappé |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a8694882595177011578-ester-exposito-sort-du-silence-sur-kylian-mbappe |access-date=2026-04-03 |website=Foot Mercato : Info Transferts Football - Actu Foot Transfert |language=fr}}</ref>

